#. [race]: id=demon
#: Naia/units/demons.cfg:12
msgid "race+female^Demoness"
msgstr "Démone"

#. [race]: id=demon
#: Naia/units/demons.cfg:13
msgid "race^Demons"
msgstr "Démons"

#. [race]: id=demon
#: Naia/units/demons.cfg:14
msgid ""
"Legend has it that at the beginning of time, powerful creatures called "
"‘demons’ governed all that existed. The Lords of Light and Darkness, seeing "
"the danger they posed for the balance of nature, banished them to a separate "
"plane of existence, trapped with no means of escape from inside. But time "
"and time again, different versions of the legend have been told by different "
"peoples in different places. Presumably, whatever small amount of truth "
"there was in the original version of the story has since been lost forever.\n"
"\n"
"Either by ignorance, or in an attempt to make sense of the fractured stories "
"gathered from Chaos prisoners, the peoples of Irdya refer more generally to "
"all the vastly heterogeneous races of Inferno by this generic designation. "
"Some go as far as to claim that normal Irdyan creatures may become ‘demonic’ "
"in some form or another, pointing at the Chaos Lorekeepers’ powers and "
"inscrutable nature."
msgstr ""
"La légende raconte qu'au commencement, de puissantes créatures appelées "
"‘démons’ gouvernaient tout ce qui existait. Les Seigneurs de la Lumière et "
"de l'Obscurité, voyant le danger pour l'équilibre de la nature, les "
"bannirent dans un plan d'existence séparé, où ils furent piégés sans aucun "
"espoir d'échappatoire à moins d'être aidés depuis l'extérieur. Mais avec le "
"temps, différentes versions de la légende ont émergé en différents endroits. "
"Il est probable que l'once de vérité existant dans la version originale de "
"cette histoire ait été définitivement perdue.\n"
"\n"
"Que ce soit par ignorance ou dans une tentative de donner un sens aux "
"fragments d'histoires arrachées aux prisonniers du Chaos, les peuples "
"d'Irdya font référence à l'ensemble hétérogène des races d'Inferno par ce "
"nom générique. Certains vont jusqu'à dire que les créatures ordinaires "
"d'Irdya pourraient devenir ‘démoniaques’ sous une certaine forme, pointant "
"les pouvoirs des Gardiens des traditions et leur nature indéfinissable."

#. [unit_type]: id=Demon, race=demon, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/demons/Fighter_Demon.cfg:5
msgid "Demon"
msgstr "Démon"

#. [unit_type]: id=Demon, race=demon, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/demons/Fighter_Demon.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Legend has it that at the beginning of time, powerful creatures called "
"‘demons’ governed all that existed. The Lords of Light and Darkness, seeing "
"the danger they posed for the balance of nature, banished them to a separate "
"plane of existence, trapped with no means of escape from inside. It would "
"take eons before the combined effort of foolish sorcerers and the most "
"dreadful Demon Lord to ever exist would allow Uria unleash her hordes on a "
"ravaged land.\n"
"\n"
"These fighter demons are nimble and sturdy creatures who have largely "
"forgone the need for armor or clothing to protect themselves from physical "
"damage. Although their sharp claws and unnatural strength allow them to tear "
"opponents apart with ease, they usually prefer wielding crude blade weapons "
"to appear even more intimidating in combat."
msgstr ""
"La légende raconte qu'au commencement, de puissantes créatures appelées "
"‘démons’ gouvernaient tout ce qui existait. Les Seigneurs de la Lumière et "
"de l'Obscurité, voyant le danger pour l'équilibre de la nature, les "
"bannirent dans un plan d'existence séparé, où ils furent piégés sans aucun "
"espoir d'échappatoire à moins d'être aidés depuis l'extérieur . Il fallut "
"une éternité pour que les efforts combinés de sorciers stupides et des "
"seigneurs démons les plus redoutables à avoir jamais existé permettent à "
"Uria d'envoyer ses hordes sur une terre ravagée.\n"
"\n"
"Ces combattants démons sont des créatures rusées et déterminées qui ont "
"largement compensé le besoin d'une armure pour se protéger des dommages "
"physiques . Bien que leurs griffes acérées et leur force surnaturelle leur "
"permettent d'en finir rapidement avec leurs adversaires, ils préfèrent "
"habituellement utiliser des armes tranchantes grossières pour paraître plus "
"intimidants au combat."

#. [female]: gender=female
#: Naia/units/demons/Fighter_Demon.cfg:107
msgid "female^Demoness"
msgstr "Démone"

#. [unit_type]: id=Demon Grunt, race=demon, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/demons/Fighter_Grunt.cfg:5
msgid "Demon Grunt"
msgstr "Grognard démoniaque"

#. [unit_type]: id=Demon Grunt, race=demon, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/demons/Fighter_Grunt.cfg:25
msgid ""
"The best demon fighters are renowned for their unrivaled strength and "
"performance under any environmental conditions. They obtain and craft new "
"weapons and armor using whatever they can salvage from defeated foes, and "
"learn new combat skills as they adapt to the land to which they are sent by "
"their overlords."
msgstr ""
"Les meilleurs guerriers démons sont renommés pour leur force et leur "
"performance sans pareille dans n'importe quelles conditions "
"environnementales. Ils obtiennent et arborent de nouvelles armes et armures "
"en utilisant ce qu'ils peuvent récupérer de leurs ennemis vaincus, et "
"assimilent de nouveaux styles de combat tout en s'adaptant au territoire où "
"ils sont envoyés par leurs suzerains."

#. [attack]: type=cold
#: Naia/units/demons/Fighter_Grunt.cfg:39
#: Naia/units/demons/Fighter_Warrior.cfg:41
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Invoker_Lorekeeper.cfg:51
msgid "infernal chill"
msgstr "froid infernal"

#. [female]: gender=female
#: Naia/units/demons/Fighter_Grunt.cfg:121
msgid "female^Demoness Grunt"
msgstr "Grognarde démoniaque"

#. [unit_type]: id=Demon Warrior, race=demon, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/demons/Fighter_Warrior.cfg:5
msgid "Demon Warrior"
msgstr "Guerrier démon"

#. [unit_type]: id=Demon Warrior, race=demon, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/demons/Fighter_Warrior.cfg:27
msgid ""
"The few natives of Irdya who have dared underestimate the might of these "
"demonic warriors have invariably suffered horrific deaths at the hands of "
"these blood-thirsty behemoths. The power of the armies of Chaos largely "
"depends on the Lorekeepers’ wisdom in selecting the best fighters to serve "
"them with their undying loyalty to Uria’s cause. But in time, a legendary "
"warrior might rise from the ranks of servility and dethrone a mighty Demon "
"Lord—even their own—and become him or herself a great vassal of Uria."
msgstr ""
"Les quelques natifs d'Irdya qui ont sous-estimé la force de ces guerriers "
"démoniaques ont invariablement souffert d'une mort horrible par la main de "
"ces êtres assoiffés de sang. La puissance des armées du Chaos dépend "
"largement de la capacité des gardiens du savoir à choisir les meilleurs "
"combattants pour les servir avec une loyauté indéfectible à la cause d'Uria. "
"Mais parfois, il arrive qu'un guerrier légendaire quitte les rangs de la "
"servitude et détrône un puissant seigneur démon, voir le sien, devenant "
"ainsi lui-même un grand vassal d'Uria."

#. [female]: gender=female
#: Naia/units/demons/Fighter_Warrior.cfg:127
msgid "female^Demoness Warrior"
msgstr "Guerrière démone"

#. [unit_type]: id=Demon Zephyr, race=demon, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/demons/Fighter_Zephyr.cfg:5
msgid "Demon Zephyr"
msgstr "Démon zéphyr"

#. [unit_type]: id=Demon Zephyr, race=demon, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/demons/Fighter_Zephyr.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Some demons go through a different maturing process and grow large webbed "
"wings, which allow them to use their enormous strength to fly across great "
"distances. As weapons and armor could only hinder them in flight, they must "
"rely on their species’ strong build, long and sharp claws, and their limited "
"control of fire to strike at their prey from above."
msgstr ""
"Certains démons suivent un processus de maturation différent et acquièrent "
"de larges ailes, leur permettant d'utiliser leur énorme force pour voler sur "
"de grandes distances. Comme les armes et armures ne peuvent que les gêner en "
"vol, ils doivent miser sur leur constitution, leurs griffes longues et "
"acérées, et leur contrôle limité du feu pour attaquer leurs proies depuis "
"les airs."

#. [female]: gender=female
#: Naia/units/demons/Fighter_Zephyr.cfg:107
msgid "female^Demoness Zephyr"
msgstr "Démone zéphyr"

#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Field Steward, race=elf
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Field_Steward.cfg:5
#, fuzzy
msgid "Elvish Field Steward"
msgstr "Chasseur elfe"

#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Field Steward, race=elf
#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Pathfinder, race=elf
#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Patrol Captain, race=elf
#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Wayfarer, race=elf
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Field_Steward.cfg:20
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Pathfinder.cfg:20
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Patrol_Captain.cfg:20
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Wayfarer.cfg:20
msgid ""
"While the elves of the Valley of Elynia have laws guaranteeing hospitality "
"to visitors from the dunes, hostile invasion attempts are far too frequent "
"for them to afford leaving their borders unguarded.\n"
"\n"
"All members of the Border Patrol have a sworn duty to elvenkind, and from a "
"very young age undergo the most rigorous training. Their diligent study and "
"practice of advanced fight and survival tactics allows them to overcome the "
"natural skills of those born amidst the eternal strife of the desert."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=blade
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Field_Steward.cfg:27
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Pathfinder.cfg:27
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Patrol_Captain.cfg:27
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Wayfarer.cfg:27
msgid "sword"
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=pierce
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Field_Steward.cfg:36
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Pathfinder.cfg:36
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Patrol_Captain.cfg:36
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Wayfarer.cfg:36
msgid "bow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Pathfinder, race=elf
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Pathfinder.cfg:5
#, fuzzy
msgid "Elvish Pathfinder"
msgstr "Chasseur elfe"

#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Patrol Captain, race=elf
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Patrol_Captain.cfg:5
#, fuzzy
msgid "Elvish Patrol Captain"
msgstr "Patrouilleur elfe"

#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Wayfarer, race=elf
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Border_Wayfarer.cfg:5
#, fuzzy
msgid "Elvish Wayfarer"
msgstr "Patrouilleur elfe"

#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Hunter, race=elf, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Hunter.cfg:5
msgid "Elvish Hunter"
msgstr "Chasseur elfe"

#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Hunter, race=elf, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Hunter.cfg:29
msgid ""
"In order to protect their lands, the forest elves of the Valley of Elynia "
"have developed new practices and formed special trained groups to patrol "
"their frontiers. Their hunters are specialized in trapping unwary opponents "
"from a safe distance to ease the task of the swordsmen."
msgstr ""
"Afin de protéger leurs terres, les elfes sylvains de la vallée d'Elynia ont "
"développé de nouvelles pratiques et formé des groupes spécialement entraînés "
"pour patrouiller le long de leurs frontières. Ces chasseurs sont spécialisés "
"pour piéger les opposants d'une distance sûre pour faciliter la tache des "
"épéistes."

#. [female]: gender=female
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Hunter.cfg:146
msgid "female^Elvish Hunter"
msgstr "Chasseresse elfe"

#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Prowler, race=elf, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Prowler.cfg:5
msgid "Elvish Prowler"
msgstr "Patrouilleur elfe"

#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Prowler, race=elf, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Prowler.cfg:34
msgid ""
"The best hunters are renowned for their skill in taking advantage of their "
"surroundings to sneak past enemies unnoticed and strike at them by surprise. "
"It is not unusual for incursion parties to be either disbanded or decimated "
"by patrol teams led by a few veteran prowlers."
msgstr ""
"Les meilleurs chasseurs sont renommés pour leur capacité à tirer profit de "
"leur environnement immédiat pour atteindre leurs ennemis et les attaquer par "
"surprise. Il n'est pas inhabituel que des incursions soient mises en déroute "
"ou même décimées par une équipe de patrouilleurs expérimentés."

#. [female]: gender=female
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Prowler.cfg:127
msgid "female^Elvish Prowler"
msgstr "Patrouilleuse elfe"

#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Trapper, race=elf, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Trapper.cfg:5
msgid "Elvish Trapper"
msgstr "Trappeur elfe"

#. [unit_type]: id=Elvish Trapper, race=elf, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Trapper.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Field experience has granted Elvish Trappers greater expertise in patrolling "
"and defending their bases, utilizing decoys and swift moves to confound "
"their enemies and attack them from behind. Their continuous training in "
"swordplay also begins to prove advantageous, allowing them to operate better "
"on their own."
msgstr ""
"L'expérience a transformé les trappeurs elfiques en véritables experts en "
"matière de patrouille et de défense de leur base, utilisant diversions et "
"mouvements rapides pour désorienter leurs ennemis et les attaquer par-"
"derrière. Ces éclaireurs sont devenus plus agiles avec une épée, les rendant "
"plus efficaces quand ils sont livrés à eux-mêmes."

#. [female]: gender=female
#: Naia/units/elves-wood/Trapper.cfg:125
msgid "female^Elvish Trapper"
msgstr "Trappeuse elfe"

#. [race]: id=faerie
#: Naia/units/faeries.cfg:5
msgid "race^Faerie"
msgstr "Fée"

#. [race]: id=faerie
#: Naia/units/faeries.cfg:6
msgid "race+male^Faerie"
msgstr "Farfadet"

#. [race]: id=faerie
#: Naia/units/faeries.cfg:7
msgid "race^Faeries"
msgstr "Fées"

#. [race]: id=faerie
#: Naia/units/faeries.cfg:8
msgid ""
"Forests, caverns, mountains, and large bodies of water are propitious places "
"to find many kinds of rare and mysterious creatures. Such environments are "
"thus preferred by the remnants of the peoples said to antedate civilized "
"life on Irdya, such as woses and merfolk, and the varied group of beings "
"more commonly known as the true faeries."
msgstr ""
"Les forêts, cavernes, montagnes et les grandes étendues d'eaux sont des "
"endroits propices pour trouver toutes sortes de créatures rares et "
"mystérieuses. De tels environnements sont donc appréciés par les vestiges "
"des peuples qui auraient précédé toute vie civilisée sur Irdya, tels que les "
"woses et les ondins, ainsi que le groupe varié de créatures connues comme "
"étant les véritables fées."

#. [unit_type]: id=Faerie Dryad, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Dryad.cfg:5
msgid "Dryad"
msgstr "Dryade"

#. [unit_type]: id=Faerie Dryad, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Dryad.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Dryads possess a closer affinity to their faerie nature than their brethren, "
"yet at times exhibit a remarkable understanding of human nature. In fact, "
"Dryads are more apt to engage the few travelers they meet in friendly "
"conversation than seduce or murder them. Some elven scholars have proposed "
"there exists a deeper connection between woodlandkind and humans as children "
"of Earth; to many, this is unthinkable. For them, to even suggest such a "
"connection between the violent, destructive humans and the ancient, "
"illustrious elves constitutes heresy.\n"
"\n"
"If there are those among the faerie with knowledge of this world’s "
"beginnings, they do not share it, preferring instead to lead peaceful, "
"modest lives. Nonetheless, the Dryads’ calm nature in no way means they are "
"powerless. Their extensive knowledge of nature and its magical arts makes "
"them a formidable opponent in any conflict."
msgstr ""
"Les dryades possèdent une plus grande affinité à leur nature féerique que "
"leurs congénères, et en même temps une remarquable compréhension de la "
"nature humaine. En fait, les dryades sont mêmes capables d'engager une "
"conversation avec les voyageurs qu'elles croisent, plutôt que de les séduire "
"et de les assassiner. Certains experts elfes ont avancé qu'il existe une "
"profonde connexion entre les races de la forêt et les humains comme enfants "
"de la terre ; pour beaucoup, c'est impensable. Pour eux, ne serait-ce que "
"suggérer une connexion entre les humains violents et destructeurs, et les "
"elfes anciens et illustres, relève de l'hérésie.\n"
"\n"
"S'il y en a parmi les fées qui possèdent la connaissance des origines du "
"monde , elles ne s'en servent pas, préférant mener une vie paisible et "
"modeste. Pour autant, la nature calme des dryades n'est pas synonyme "
"d'impuissance. Leurs connaissances étendues de la nature et de ses arts "
"magiques en font de formidables adversaires dans un conflit."

#. [attack]: type=fire
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Dryad.cfg:33 Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Faerie.cfg:31
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Faerie_Spirit.cfg:39
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Sprite.cfg:30
msgid "fire aura"
msgstr "aura de feu"

#. [attack]: type=fire
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Dryad.cfg:42 Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Faerie.cfg:40
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Faerie_Spirit.cfg:51
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Sprite.cfg:39
msgid "mystic fire"
msgstr "feu mystique"

#. [unit_type]: id=Fire Faerie, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Faerie.cfg:5
msgid "Fire Faerie"
msgstr "Fée de feu"

#. [unit_type]: id=Fire Faerie, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Faerie.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Forest faeries rarely take part in wars and conflicts, preferring instead to "
"dance and frolic in their forest homes. They will, however, defend these to "
"the death; to this end, the forest elves have proven allies of convenience. "
"The elves themselves have long had respect for those with a close affinity "
"with the Arcane Flame. It is due to this close relationship that faeries "
"will sometimes be found by the elves’ side in times of great need.\n"
"\n"
"The more experienced faeries possess an even greater mastery of the fire "
"element, allowing them to hurl balls of raging fire at their enemies, or to "
"ignite them with a single touch. Some are even said to eventually burn away "
"their corporeal forms entirely, becoming a spirit born of the rage of the "
"Flame."
msgstr ""
"Les fées sylvaines s'impliquent rarement dans les guerres et autres "
"conflits, préférant danser et s'amuser dans leurs demeures forestières. "
"Elles défendront néanmoins celles-ci jusqu'à la mort ; de ce fait, les elfes "
"sylvains peuvent se révéler être des alliés de circonstance. Les elfes eux-"
"mêmes ont depuis longtemps cultivé le plus grand respect envers ces "
"créatures avec une telle affinité avec la Flamme des Arcanes. C'est à cause "
"de ce lien étroit que les fées peuvent parfois être vues aux côtés des elfes "
"en temps de besoin.\n"
"\n"
"Les fées les plus expérimentées possèdent une plus grande maîtrise du feu, "
"leur permettant de l'envoyer en rafales sur leurs ennemis, ou de les "
"enflammer par simple contact. Quelques-unes auraient même entièrement brûlé "
"leur corps physique, devenant des esprits nés de la colère de la Flamme."

#. [unit_type]: id=Faerie Spirit, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Faerie_Spirit.cfg:5
msgid "Forest Spirit"
msgstr "Esprit de la forêt"

#. [unit_type]: id=Faerie Spirit, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Faerie_Spirit.cfg:31
msgid ""
"One of the greatest mysteries of life is the true nature of Faerie, a domain "
"of existence beyond the grasp of mortal creatures and the source of a power "
"said to predate Irdya’s creation by an immensurable eternity. Even though "
"elves and faeries have an innate affinity to the mystical energy within, "
"their ability to channel it is severely constrained by their attachment to "
"the physical realm. Breaking free of those bindings and fully embracing the "
"arcane flame is not without its drawbacks, however.\n"
"\n"
"These faerie phantasms are occasionally seen aimlessly wandering the forests "
"during the twilight. Their warped minds are no longer able to discern our "
"reality from theirs, and only gradually fading memories keep them anchored "
"to the domain of the living."
msgstr ""
"L'un des grands mystères de la vie est la véritable nature féerique, un "
"domaine de l'existence hors de portée des mortels et source d'un pouvoir qui "
"aurait précédé la création d'Irdya d'une éternité incommensurable. Même si "
"les elfes et les fées ont une capacité innée à canaliser cette énergie "
"mystique, elle reste sévèrement limitée par leur lien avec le monde "
"physique. Briser ces liens et embrasser totalement la flamme des arcanes "
"n'est toutefois pas sans conséquences.\n"
"\n"
"Ces phantasmes féeriques sont occasionnellement vus en train de parcourir "
"les forêts durant le crépuscule. Leur esprit ne peut plus distinguer notre "
"réalité de la leur, et seule leur mémoire vacillante les relie encore au "
"monde des vivants."

#. [unit_type]: id=Faerie Hamadryad, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Hamadryad.cfg:5
msgid "Hamadryad"
msgstr "Hamadryade"

#. [unit_type]: id=Faerie Hamadryad, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Hamadryad.cfg:34
msgid ""
"Elven lore tells of faerie creatures back in the Golden Age who achieved an "
"even more intimate connection to the earth than their fellow dryads and "
"forest phantoms, able to assume the shape of majestic trees and enjoy an "
"exceedingly long, albeit solitary existence in the deepest forests of "
"Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Despite the name, the “hamadryads” were rumored to have more in common with "
"woses than their comparatively mundane sisters. Their command of nature was "
"unparalleled and said to surpass even the mightiest sylphs of yore, "
"instilling such awe into them that some elven communities revered them as "
"protector deities. To defile the sanctity of their domain—be it with fire, "
"bloodshed or the felling of healthy trees—was considered a sin beyond "
"redemption.\n"
"\n"
"Finding one of these mythical nymphs in humanoid form anywhere other than "
"the heart of the forest is completely unheard of and would necessitate a "
"magic disturbance of an unprecedented scale, or a highly improbable fluke."
msgstr ""
"L'histoire des elfes mentionne l'existence de créatures féériques durant "
"l'Âge d'Or qui auraient développé un lien à la terre encore plus étroit que "
"leurs compagnons dryades et fantômes sylvestres, et qu'elles étaient "
"capables de prendre la forme d'arbres majestueux et de profiter d'une "
"existence extraordinaire longue, bien que solitaire, dans les plus profonds "
"recoins des forêts d'Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Malgré leur nom, il est dit que les \"hamadryades\" sont plus proches des "
"woses que de leurs sœurs comparativement banales. Leur maitrise de la nature "
"était si inégalée qu'elle aurait même surpassé les sylphides d'antan, "
"suscitant tant d'admiration que plusieurs communautés elfiques les auraient "
"révérées comme une forme de déité protectrice. Profaner la sainteté de leur "
"domaine—que ce soit avec du feu, du sang ou l'abattage d'arbres vigoureux—"
"était considéré comme un péché au-delà de toute rédemption.\n"
"\n"
"Parvenir à trouver l'une de ces nymphes mythiques sous forme humaine "
"ailleurs qu'au cœur de la forêt relève du mirage, ça nécessiterait une "
"perturbation magique sans précédent, ou un coup de chance hautement "
"improbable."

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Hamadryad.cfg:44
msgid "suffocate"
msgstr "étouffement"

#. [unit_type]: id=Faerie Sprite, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Sprite.cfg:5
msgid "Sprite"
msgstr "Lutin"

#. [unit_type]: id=Faerie Sprite, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/units/faeries/Fire_Sprite.cfg:20
msgid ""
"To a creature of the forests, fire is a mortal enemy, yet to the Faerie "
"Sprites, it is a weapon strangely antithetical to their wooded nature. "
"Though not much is otherwise factually known about the Faerie race, rare as "
"they are and despite their numbers having grown since the Fall, they have "
"always been viewed as gentle, mischievous beings, if perhaps a little too "
"apt to play with the hearts of men.\n"
"\n"
"Travelers who have encountered them speak of beautiful elfin women clad in "
"simple robes, their gossamer-thin wings glinting like jewels in starlight. "
"Rare is the man — or woman — whose breath is not lost upon the sight of "
"these beings, and neither are their advances spurned. Some awaken the next "
"morning alone, and move on, only to find a child on their doorsteps months "
"later. A more unlucky number never again see the light of day; they are "
"often found dead, lying contentedly amongst the fallen leaves.\n"
"\n"
"Yet despite their reputations, faeries are by no means evil. Perhaps it is "
"their strange sense of impish humor that leads them to do these things, or "
"perhaps something deeper in their nature."
msgstr ""
"Pour une créature de la forêt, le feu est un ennemi mortel, pour une fée, "
"c'est donc une arme étrangement antithétique à leur nature sylvaine. Bien "
"que rien de factuel ne soit connu de la race féerique, elles sont rares et "
"bien que leur nombre ait augmenté depuis la Chute, elles sont toujours vues "
"comme des êtres gentils, malicieux, et peut-être un peu trop prompts à jouer "
"avec le cœur des hommes.\n"
"\n"
"Les voyageurs qui les ont rencontrées parlent de magnifiques femmes elfes "
"vêtues de simples robes, leurs ailes fines et translucides brillant comme "
"des joyaux à la lumière des étoiles. Rare sont les hommes — ou femmes — qui "
"n'ont pas eu le souffle coupé à leur vue, et qui ont su rejeter leurs "
"propositions. Certains se réveillent le lendemain, seuls, et repartent, "
"avant de trouver un enfant à leur porte des mois après. Les moins chanceux "
"ne revoient jamais la lumière du jour ; ils sont souvent retrouvés morts "
"allongés, le sourire aux lèvres.\n"
"\n"
"Malgré leur réputation, les fées ne sont pas de nature mauvaise. Peut-être "
"est-ce leur étrange sens de l'humour qui les amène à faire ces choses ou "
"bien quelque chose de plus profond dans leur nature."

#. [race]: id=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans.cfg:5
msgid "race^Aragwaith"
msgstr "Aragwaith"

#. [race]: id=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans.cfg:6
msgid "race+female^Aragwaith"
msgstr "Aragwaith"

#. [race]: id=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans.cfg:7
msgid "race^Aragwaithi"
msgstr "Aragwaiths"

#. [race]: id=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans.cfg:12
msgid ""
"During most of the Golden Age, the humans who inhabited the Great Continent "
"were mostly Wesnothians, divided across various territories such as the "
"Northlands, Elensefar and the kingdom of Wesnoth itself. However, there was "
"once a time of great strife during which a new race of humans started to "
"appear from nowhere. They were the ‘Aragwaithi’, which meant ‘noble’ in "
"their native language.\n"
"\n"
"It has been since then rumored that they came from the Vast Sea to settle in "
"Wesnoth. They mostly lived as mercenaries in that time, until the Fall. "
"After that, they supposedly moved to the northmost lands of the Continent, "
"were the sands could not reach, and the green could survive.\n"
"\n"
"Albeit being humans, many of their customs and racial features are strongly "
"reminiscent of elves. Their sages have a mastery of magic that is not to be "
"underestimated on the battlefield."
msgstr ""
"Durant la majeure partie de l'Âge d'Or, les humains qui habitaient le grand "
"continent étaient pour la plupart wesnothiens, répartis entre différents "
"territoires tels que les pays du Nord, Elensefar et le royaume de Wesnoth "
"lui-même. Cependant, il y eut à un moment un grand conflit au cours duquel "
"une nouvelle tribu humaine inopinée fit son apparition. Ses membres se "
"nommaient « aragwaiths », ce qui signifie « noble » dans leur langue "
"maternelle.\n"
"\n"
"D'après les rumeurs, ils seraient venus du Grand Océan pour s'installer à "
"Wesnoth. À cette époque, ils vivaient pour la plupart en tant que "
"mercenaires, jusqu'à la Chute. Après cela, ils se seraient installés sur les "
"terres de l'extrême Nord du continent, que le sable ne pouvait atteindre et "
"où les plantes pouvaient encore survivre.\n"
"\n"
"Bien qu'ils soient humains, beaucoup de leurs coutumes et de leurs "
"caractéristiques raciales sont étonnamment similaires à celles des elfes. "
"Leurs sages ont une maîtrise de la magie qui ne doit pas être sous-estimée "
"sur le champ de bataille."

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Ancient Banner, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Ancient_Banner.cfg:5
msgid "Ancient Banner"
msgstr "Bannière ancienne"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Ancient Banner, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Ancient_Banner.cfg:30
msgid "TODO"
msgstr "À faire"

#. [attack]: type=blade
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Ancient_Banner.cfg:44
msgid "scythe"
msgstr "faux"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Archer, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Archer.cfg:5
msgid "Archer"
msgstr "Archer"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Archer, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Archer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The Aragwaithi are a noble people, fragile in body, but their training makes "
"them among the more deadly denizens of this world. Their archers are no "
"exception. Their skills with a bow are comparable to those of some elves, "
"and they are remarkably quick with their daggers."
msgstr ""
"Les aragwaiths sont un peuple noble, de constitution fragile, mais que "
"l'entraînement transforme en l'un des plus redoutables peuples de ce monde. "
"Leurs archers ne font pas exception. Leur habileté à l'arc est comparable à "
"celle des elfes et ils sont d'une rapidité exceptionnelle avec leurs dagues."

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Captain, race=aragwaith, description=
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Captain.cfg:5
msgid "Captain"
msgstr "Capitaine"

#. [attack]: type=pierce
#. [attack]: type=blade
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Captain.cfg:30
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Captain.cfg:39
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Flagbearer.cfg:30
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Flagbearer.cfg:39
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Slayer.cfg:25
msgid "glaive"
msgstr "vouge"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Eagle Master, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Eagle_Master.cfg:5
msgid "Eagle Master"
msgstr "Maître des aigles"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Eagle Master, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Eagle_Master.cfg:19
msgid ""
"With experience, Eagle riders become more skilled and the relation with "
"their winged friend become so strong that they act as one. As Eagle masters, "
"they no longer need to give orders to their mounts, those anticipate them."
msgstr ""
"Avec de la pratique, les chevaucheurs d'aigles deviennent plus habiles et "
"leur relation avec leur ami ailé devient si forte qu'ils agissent tel un "
"seul être. Les maîtres des aigles n'ont ainsi plus besoin de donner d'ordres "
"à leur monture, qui les anticipe."

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Eagle_Master.cfg:36
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Eagle_Rider.cfg:32
msgid "prey crush"
msgstr "broyage de proie"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Eagle Rider, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Eagle_Rider.cfg:5
msgid "Eagle Rider"
msgstr "Chevaucheur d'aigle"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Eagle Rider, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Eagle_Rider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Some Aragwaithi youths take young eagles as a pet. These are not the common "
"eagles, but a race of noble, giant birds of prey. When they are grown "
"enough, they usually willing to serve as a mount for their best friend, and "
"their young mates learn the art of riding these giant birds."
msgstr ""
"Certains jeunes aragwaiths prennent de jeunes aigles comme animaux de "
"compagnie. Ce ne sont pas des aigles communs, mais une race de gigantesques "
"et nobles rapaces qui acceptent, en général après avoir suffisamment grandi, "
"de servir de monture à leur meilleur ami. Leur jeune compagnon apprend l'art "
"de les monter."

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Flagbearer, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Flagbearer.cfg:5
msgid "Flagbearer"
msgstr "Porte-étendard"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Flagbearer, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Flagbearer.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Flagbearers are the leaders on the battlefield. They wield large banners to "
"lead and inspire the soldiers. They are also skilled with the glaive, which "
"makes them dangerous in combat too."
msgstr ""
"Les porte-étendards sont les meneurs sur le champ de bataille. Ils arborent "
"de grandes bannières pour mener et inspirer les soldats. Ils sont aussi "
"entraînés au maniement de la vouge, les rendant également dangereux au "
"combat."

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Greatbow, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Greatbow.cfg:5
msgid "Greatbow"
msgstr "Grand-arc"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Greatbow, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Greatbow.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Finally moving on from the dirk and dagger to the sword, the Greatbows are "
"superior to the Strongbows in melee combat, although not as much as the "
"Slayers. Their bows are masterpieces of military craftsmanship, designed and "
"built by their users to their own particular requirements over the span of "
"several months. Due to the large strength required to draw these bows, any "
"person other than the owner trying to use them could suffer serious injuries."
msgstr ""
"Abandonnant enfin la dague et le poignard au profit de l'épée, les grands-"
"arcs sont supérieurs aux puissants-arcs en combat rapproché bien qu'ils "
"restent toutefois dominés par les massacreurs. Leurs arcs sont des "
"merveilles d'artisanat militaire, pensés et conçus pour accommoder "
"spécifiquement leurs besoins au terme de plusieurs mois de travail. En "
"raison de la force nécessaire pour bander de tels arcs, toute autre personne "
"voulant les utiliser s'expose à de sérieux dangers pour son corps."

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Guard, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Guard.cfg:5
msgid "Guard"
msgstr "Garde"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Guard, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Guard.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Chosen from among the toughest Swordsmen, Aragwaith Guards opt to forgo "
"their mobility in favor of the advantages that armor brings to their "
"survivability. Whether posted to ceremonial units during times of peace, or "
"to the battlefield during war, their role is always the same: defending "
"their country’s nobility."
msgstr ""
"Choisis parmi les spadassins les plus endurcis, les gardes aragwaiths "
"choisissent d'abandonner leur mobilité en échange de la protection qu'offre "
"leur nouvelle armure. Qu'ils soient postés en tant qu'unités cérémonielles "
"en temps de paix ou sur le champ de bataille en temps de guerre, leur rôle "
"est toujours le même : défendre la noblesse de leur nation."

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Guardian, race=aragwaith, description=
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Guardian.cfg:5
msgid "Guardian"
msgstr "Gardien"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Lancer, race=aragwaith, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Lancer.cfg:5
msgid "Lancer"
msgstr "Lancier"

#. [female]: gender=female
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Lancer.cfg:144
msgid "female^Lancer"
msgstr "Lancière"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Longswordsman, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Longswordsman.cfg:5
msgid "Longswordsman"
msgstr "Escrimeur"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Longswordsman, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Longswordsman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"While Aragwaithi Swordsmen seem uncannily skilled to blade-wielders of other "
"races, the Aragwaithi reserve their own admiration for Longswordsmen. These "
"warriors have become so adept at the arts of thrust and parry that they have "
"adopted a longer blade than the Swordsmen, yet they are able to wield it "
"with equal grace and skill."
msgstr ""
"Malgré le talent supérieur de leurs spadassins, les aragwaiths réservent "
"toute leur admiration aux escrimeurs. Ces guerriers sont si habiles pour "
"parer et pour frapper d'estoc et de taille qu'ils préfèrent porter une épée "
"plus longue, toujours maniée avec autant d'aisance et de grâce."

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Pikeman, race=aragwaith, description=
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Pikeman.cfg:5
msgid "Pikeman"
msgstr "Piquier"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Scout, race=aragwaith, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Scout.cfg:5
msgid "Scout"
msgstr "Éclaireur"

#. [female]: gender=female
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Scout.cfg:65
msgid "female^Scout"
msgstr "Éclaireuse"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Shield Guard, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Shield_Guard.cfg:5
msgid "Shield Guard"
msgstr "Garde bouclier"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Shield Guard, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Shield_Guard.cfg:27
msgid ""
"These warriors wear the old shields of their ancients. These ancients could "
"hold the line in the great battles until the reinforcements arrived, but "
"they paid a high price, not many survived the battle and many others died "
"through their strong wounds. Now only the best warriors are allowed to carry "
"these ancient shields to remind the world and to honor these brave man and "
"their sacrifice."
msgstr ""
"Ces guerriers portent les antiques boucliers de leurs ancêtres qui pouvaient "
"tenir le rang lors des grandes batailles jusqu'à l'arrivée des renforts. "
"Ceux-ci l'ont payé cher, car peu ont survécu et beaucoup sont morts suite à "
"leurs blessures. Aujourd'hui, seuls les meilleurs guerriers ont le droit de "
"brandir le bouclier des anciens en hommage à la vie de ces gens courageux, "
"ainsi que leur honneur et leur sacrifice."

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Silver Shield, race=aragwaith, gender=male,female
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Silver_Shield.cfg:5
msgid "Silver Shield"
msgstr "Bouclier d'argent"

#. [female]: gender=female
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Silver_Shield.cfg:190
msgid "female^Silver Shield"
msgstr "Bouclier d'argent"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Slayer, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Slayer.cfg:5
msgid "Slayer"
msgstr "Massacreur"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Slayer, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Slayer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"While improving only marginally on the power of their bow, the Slayer "
"abandons the blade in favor of training with a glaive, improving his skills "
"in hand-to-hand combat. He is not as rugged as others of comparable skill, "
"but far deadlier."
msgstr ""
"Alors qu'il ne développe que peu son habileté à l'arc, le massacreur "
"abandonne le couteau pour s'entraîner au maniement de la vouge, améliorant "
"ainsi ses capacités en combat rapproché. Il n'est pas aussi acharné que "
"d'autres, aussi compétents que lui, mais bien plus mortel."

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Sorceress, race=aragwaith, gender=female
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Sorceress.cfg:5
msgid "female^Sorceress"
msgstr "Sorcière"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Sorceress, race=aragwaith, gender=female
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Sorceress.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The mighty Aragwaith Sorceresses are agile like the wind. They can confound "
"their opponents by standing in front of them seemingly defenseless; once the "
"attacker hits, they realize their victim is actually behind them, ready to "
"land her own killing blow. Because of their vast and intimate knowledge of "
"both defensive and offensive magic, even the higher ranks of the Aragwaithi "
"regard these women with great respect and caution."
msgstr ""
"Les puissantes sorcières aragwaith sont aussi agiles que le vent. Elles sont "
"capables de tromper leurs adversaires alors qu'elles apparaissent sans "
"défense devant eux ; ce n'est que lorsque l'attaquant tente de porter un "
"coup qu'il réalise que sa victime est en fait dans son dos, prête à lui "
"porter le coup de grâce. En raison de leur vastes connaissances en magie "
"aussi bien offensive que défensive, même les plus hauts rangs des aragwaiths "
"font preuve de respect et de prudence envers ces femmes."

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Spearman, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Spearman.cfg:5
msgid "Spearman"
msgstr "Porte-lance"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Spearman, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Spearman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The less dextrous and stronger Aragwaith take up the spear. Useful in "
"hunting, this weapon is also deadly on the battlefield. Many impetuous "
"knights have found themselves or their mounts impaled on the point of an "
"Aragwaithi spear."
msgstr ""
"Les aragwaiths possédant plus de force que de dextérité choisissent la "
"lance. Dangereuse à la chasse, cette arme est également mortelle sur un "
"champ de bataille. Beaucoup de chevaliers impétueux se sont retrouvés "
"empalés au bout d'une lance aragwaith."

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Strongbow, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Strongbow.cfg:5
msgid "Strongbow"
msgstr "Puissant-arc"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Strongbow, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Strongbow.cfg:17
msgid ""
"By wielding a stronger bow and training almost constantly, the Aragwaith "
"Strongbow fires a far deadlier shot than the average archer. Their dirks are "
"longer than the daggers used by the typical archer, and they wield them far "
"more effectively."
msgstr ""
"En s'équipant d'un arc plus puissant et en s'entraînant presque constamment, "
"le puissant-arc aragwaith décoche une flèche bien plus mortelle qu'un archer "
"ordinaire. Leurs couteaux sont plus longs que les dagues utilisées par les "
"archers classiques et ils les manient bien plus efficacement."

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Swordsman, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Swordsman.cfg:5
msgid "Swordsman"
msgstr "Spadassin"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Swordsman, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Swordsman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"While the Aragwaithi are slight of body, they are also fast and nimble. "
"These abilities, coupled with the intensive training given to the Aragwaith "
"military, make for superb swordsmen. Swordsmen are clad in light chain mail "
"— the better to resist the blades of their enemies."
msgstr ""
"Bien que graciles, les aragwaiths sont rapides et agiles. Ces "
"caractéristiques, couplées avec l'entraînement intensif dispensé aux "
"soldats, en font de formidables combattants à l'épée. Les spadassins sont "
"vêtus d'une cotte de mailles légère, ce qui est le mieux pour résister aux "
"lames ennemies."

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Swordsmaster, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Swordsmaster.cfg:5
msgid "Swordsmaster"
msgstr "Maître escrimeur"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Swordsmaster, race=aragwaith
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Swordsmaster.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Aragwaith Swordsmasters have endured years of rigorous military training, "
"and survived countless ferocious battles. Their swordplay prowess is "
"regarded with awe even by those few foes who have witnessed it and lived to "
"tell the tale. Upon attaining the rank and the reputation that comes with "
"it, they take up responsibility for teaching the young, passing the martial "
"traditions of the Aragwaithi onto future generations."
msgstr ""
"Les maîtres escrimeurs aragwaith ont enduré des années d'entrainement "
"militaire rigoureurx et ils ont survécu à nombre de batailles féroces. Leur "
"jeu d'escrime est révéré par les quelques adversaires qui ont survécu à "
"l'affrontement contre l'un de ces maîtres. Quand ils atteignent ce rang et "
"la réputation qui lui est associée, ils prennent la responsabilité "
"d'enseigner aux générations futures, perpétrant ainsi les traditions "
"martiales des aragwaith à travers les âges."

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Witch, race=aragwaith, gender=female
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Witch.cfg:6
msgid "female^Witch"
msgstr "Apprentie sorcière"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Witch, race=aragwaith, gender=female
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Witch.cfg:78
msgid ""
"The increasingly rare magically-gifted noblewomen of the Aragwaithi function "
"as the lorekeepers of their unique civilization, possessing vast knowledge "
"about the history of Irdya and the many trials faced by their ancestors. But "
"the path to reach their status and earn the Grand Council’s trust and "
"respect is arduous, and much of their lives is spent training in the "
"marches, far away from their kin. In those parts, the ability to create and "
"control flames is highly versatile, as well as the mastery of the arts of "
"healing."
msgstr ""
"Les rares femmes nobles douées de magie chez les aragwaiths ont la fonction "
"de gardiennes du savoir de cette civilisation unique, détenant de vastes "
"connaissances sur l'histoire d'Irdya et les nombreuses épreuves qu'ont "
"affronté leurs ancêtres. Mais la voie à suivre pour acquérir ce statut ainsi "
"que gagner la confiance et le respect du Grand Conseil est ardue, et elles "
"dévouent la majeure partie de leur vie à s'entrainer aux frontières, loin "
"des leurs. En ces lieux, la capacité de créer et contrôler le feu est "
"hautement polyvalente, de même que la maîtrise des soins."

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Witch.cfg:127
msgid "kick"
msgstr "coup"

#. [unit_type]: id=Aragwaith Wizard, race=aragwaith, gender=female, description=
#: Naia/units/humans/Aragwaith_Wizard.cfg:5
msgid "female^Wizard"
msgstr "Magicienne"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Bowman, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Bowman.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Bowman"
msgstr "Archer du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Bowman, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Bowman.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Since time immemorial, humans have used and perfected the bow and arrow for "
"hunting and defense. Even after the Fall, it continues to be the cheapest "
"and most effective weapon a military can afford for its lowest-ranking "
"soldiers. Archers seldom have adequate training or equipment to be effective "
"in combat at close quarters, but they are nonetheless capable of defending "
"themselves should the situation call for it."
msgstr ""
"Depuis des temps immémoriaux, les humains ont perfectionné leurs arcs et "
"leurs flèches pour la chasse et la défense. Même après la Chute, ça reste "
"l'arme la moins coûteuse et la plus efficace pour équiper les soldats de "
"base d'une armée. Les archers ont rarement un entraînement et un équipement "
"adaptés au combat rapproché, mais ils sont quand même capables de se "
"défendre en cas de besoin."

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Cataphract, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Cataphract.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Cataphract"
msgstr "Cataphractaire du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Cataphract, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Cataphract.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Cataphracts are held in utmost respect by the Chaos military and serve as "
"the legions’ fearsome standard-bearers. When not carrying the Chaos flag "
"into battle, they are often seen swiftly traversing the blood-stained "
"battlefields to deliver news, commands, and supplies. Their most striking "
"aspect is the symbiotic relationship they share with their mounts, however. "
"Gentler emotions are seldom found amongst the Chaos ranks, but these riders "
"have been known to pause and mourn their fallen steeds, even amidst the "
"carnage of battle."
msgstr ""
"Les cataphractaires sont tenus en grand respect par le corps armé de "
"l'Empire du Chaos, dont ils constituent les porte-étendards les plus "
"redoutés. Quand ils ne portent pas la bannière du Chaos durant la bataille, "
"ils sont parfois vus traversant le champ de bataille ensanglanté pour "
"délivrer des nouvelles, des ordres et des provisions. L'aspect le plus "
"frappant chez eux est la relation symbiotique qu'ils entretiennent avec "
"leurs montures. Les émotions plus douces sont très peu observées dans les "
"rangs du Chaos, mais ces cavaliers sont réputés pour s'arrêter et pleurer "
"leur chevaux tombés, même au beau milieu de la bataille."

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Cavalier, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Cavalier.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Cavalier"
msgstr "Cavalier du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Cavalier, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Cavalier.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A rider and its mount achieve their maximum potential once they learn to "
"trust each other and act in unison. Even if it may seem unusual at first "
"glance, there are such horsemen fighting under Uria’s banner, and they treat "
"their companions as an extension of themselves in all regards."
msgstr ""
"Un cavalier et sa monture atteignent leur potentiel maximum une fois qu'ils "
"se font mutuellement confiance. Même si cela peut sembler inhabituel, de "
"tels cavaliers combattent bel et bien sous la bannière d'Uria, et ils "
"traitent leurs compagnons comme une extension d'eux-mêmes."

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Crossbowman, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Crossbowman.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Crossbowman"
msgstr "Arbalétrier du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Crossbowman, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Crossbowman.cfg:23
msgid ""
"While most bowmen at the Chaos Empire’s service choose to specialize further "
"in their craft with larger and more powerful bows, some opt for a less "
"conventional approach to attaining greater combat prowess. These soldiers "
"not only replace their rustic bows with crossbows — an absolute luxury for "
"an army which can barely afford full body armor — but they also trade their "
"short swords for heavier axes. While this does improve their efficacy in "
"battle to some extent, it does so at the expense of speed and accuracy."
msgstr ""
"Bien que la plupart des archers de l'Empire du Chaos se spécialisent dans "
"l'utilisation de grands et puissants arcs, certains optent pour une approche "
"moins conventionnelle. Ces soldats non seulement remplacent leurs arcs "
"rustiques par des arbalètes, un luxe absolu dans une armée peinant à "
"pourvoir une armure complète, mais ils échangent également leurs épées "
"courtes contre des haches lourdes. Bien que cela améliore leur efficacité au "
"combat jusqu'à un certain point, ils perdent alors en vitesse et en "
"précision."

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Arbalestier, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Crossbowman_Arbalestier.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Arbalestier"
msgstr "Maître arbalétrier du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Arbalestier, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Crossbowman_Arbalestier.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Going a step further than most, these elite Chaos soldiers are equipped with "
"a more sophisticated variation on the basic crossbow, able to shoot bolts "
"with much greater penetrating force. Because of the increased reload times "
"and maintenance cost, these ‘arbalests’ are rarely seen on the battlefield "
"in an active role, their owners often carrying them unloaded as a status "
"symbol instead."
msgstr ""
"Atteignant un stade plus avancé que la plupart, ces soldats d'élite du Chaos "
"sont équipés avec une variante plus sophistiquée de l'arbalète, capable de "
"propulser des traits avec une bien plus grande force de pénétration. À cause "
"des temps de rechargement plus longs et du coût d'entretien, ces 'arbalètes' "
"sont rarement employées sur le champ de bataille, leurs propriétaires "
"préférant souvent les montrer non chargées comme symbole de leur statut."

#. [attack]: type=pierce
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Crossbowman_Arbalestier.cfg:39
msgid "arbalest"
msgstr "arbalète"

#. [unit_type]: id=Dark Knight, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Dark_Knight.cfg:5
msgid "Knight of Chaos"
msgstr "Chevalier du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Dark Knight, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Dark_Knight.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Mastering the art of dual wielding is no small feat in and of itself, but "
"its applications in real combat are limited by the impracticality of "
"coordinating swings and balancing the wielder’s weight while under pressure. "
"This hardly deters Chaos infantries from trying, however, usually with "
"decent results. To inexperienced opponents, the mere sight of an approaching "
"man suited in full armor hurling guttural screams is terrifying enough "
"without him furiously swinging a sword and axe in either hand."
msgstr ""
"Maîtriser l'art du maniement d'armes pairées n'est déjà pas un mince "
"exploit, mais ses applications en combat réel sont en plus limitées par la "
"difficulté de coordonner ses coups tout en maintenant son équilibre face aux "
"attaques adverses. Cela n'empêche pourtant pas l'infanterie du Chaos "
"d'essayer, souvent avec des résultats honnêtes. Pour des adversaires "
"inexpérimentés, la seule vue d'un homme en armure hurlant de façon gutturale "
"est suffisamment terrifiante sans qu'il ne manie furieusement une épée et "
"une hache dans chaque main."

#. [unit_type]: id=Doom Guard, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Doom_Guard.cfg:5
msgid "Doom Guard"
msgstr "Garde infernal"

#. [unit_type]: id=Doom Guard, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Doom_Guard.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Although the Chaos Empire is a staunch believer in the principle of defense "
"through offense, its leadership is also well aware of the importance of "
"defending its borders against hostile incursions, as well as the occasional "
"civil revolt. Guards tasked with the protection of the Empire’s strongholds "
"are provided with specially-crafted armor and enjoy privileges normally "
"reserved only for those who have proven their worth in battle. They are also "
"occasionally granted troops and assigned to assault missions whenever a "
"considerable amount of resistance may be expected."
msgstr ""
"Bien que l'Empire du Chaos soit un fervent défenseur de l'adage \"La "
"meilleure défense, c'est l'attaque\", ses chefs sont également conscients de "
"l'importance de défendre ses frontières contre les incursions hostiles, ou "
"de faire face aux révoltes occasionnelles. Les gardes assignés à la "
"protection des places fortes de l'empire sont équipés d'une armure spéciale "
"et profitent de privilèges normalement réservés à ceux qui ont prouvé leur "
"valeur sur le champ de bataille. Ils sont aussi occasionnellement "
"réquisitionnés pour des missions d'assaut si une forte résistance est à "
"prévoir."

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Doom_Guard.cfg:34
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Hell_Guardian.cfg:35
msgid "shield"
msgstr "bouclier"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Headhunter, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Headhunter.cfg:5
msgid "Headhunter"
msgstr "Chasseur de têtes"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Headhunter, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Headhunter.cfg:25
msgid ""
"The Chaos Empire relies extensively on its charismatic Lorekeepers to "
"attract and convert outsiders — chiefly barbarians — to its cause. Those who "
"lack the ability or knowledge to join the ranks of the Chaos Magi are given "
"the most basic equipment and assigned to raiding missions where their "
"undisciplined brutality may be put to use to terrorize and confuse their "
"victims, often at the cost of their own lives."
msgstr ""
"L'Empire du Chaos repose essentiellement sur ses charismatiques gardiens du "
"savoir pour attirer et convertir les chefs barbares à sa cause. Ceux "
"dépourvus de capacités ou de connaissances pour rejoindre les rangs des "
"mages du Chaos sont dotés de l'équipement le plus basique et assignés aux "
"raids, où leur brutalité peut servir à terroriser leurs victimes, souvent au "
"prix de leur propre vie."

#. [unit_type]: id=Hell Guardian, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Hell_Guardian.cfg:5
msgid "Hell Guardian"
msgstr "Gardien des enfers"

#. [unit_type]: id=Hell Guardian, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Hell_Guardian.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Only the very best guards in the Empire’s service are allowed access to "
"equipment forged by blacksmiths from Inferno. These men are said to be able "
"to withstand a rockslide if need be, protected by their stalwart devotion to "
"the ruling lords of Inferno."
msgstr ""
"Seuls les meilleurs gardes au service de l'Empire sont autorisés à porter "
"des équipements forgés par les artisans d'Inferno. Ces hommes sont dits "
"capable de résister à un éboulement de roche si besoin est, protégés par "
"leur indéfectible dévotion aux seigneurs d'Inferno."

#. [unit_type]: id=Hell Overlord, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Hell_Overlord.cfg:5
msgid "Overlord"
msgstr "Haut seigneur"

#. [unit_type]: id=Hell Overlord, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Hell_Overlord.cfg:23
msgid ""
"There are very few things able to make Chaos soldiers cower in fear, and "
"even fewer humans who have earned the genuine respect of the demon lords of "
"Inferno. While their subordinates torture and kill for pleasure, the Chaos "
"Overlords hardly ever participate in battle, instead preferring to observe "
"the action from a safe distance. On the exceedingly rare occasions where "
"they do join the fray, they perform in an almost mechanical fashion, mowing "
"down anything that gets in their way without even attempting to dodge enemy "
"fire. It is because of their stoic disposition that many — enemies and "
"allies alike — speculate that they have surrendered their very souls to Uria "
"in exchange for their unnatural strength and resilience.\n"
"\n"
"Suffice it to say, only someone who has somehow drawn the ire of the Chaos "
"Empire would ever find themselves facing a Chaos Overlord on the battle "
"field."
msgstr ""
"Il y a très peu de choses capables d'effrayer les soldats du Chaos, et "
"encore moins d'hommes à avoir gagné le respect des seigneurs démons "
"d'Inferno. Tandis que leurs subordonnés torturent et tuent pour le plaisir, "
"les haut seigneurs du chaos participent rarement aux combats, préférant "
"observer l'action en sureté. Dans les très rares occasions où ils se "
"joignent à la mêlée, ils pratiquent un style quasi mécanique, écrasant ce "
"qui est en travers de leur route sans même chercher à esquiver le feu "
"ennemi. C'est à cause de ce comportement stoïque que beaucoup pensent qu'ils "
"ont vendu leurs âmes à Uria en échange de leur force et leur résistance "
"surnaturelles.\n"
"\n"
"De ce fait, à moins de susciter l'ire ardente de l'Empire du Chaos, aucun "
"combattant n'est assez infortuné pour croiser la route d'un haut seigneur du "
"chaos sur le champ de bataille."

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Invader, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Invader.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Invader"
msgstr "Envahisseur du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Invader, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Invader.cfg:26
msgid ""
"These dark soldiers fight for a cause they mostly ignore, many of them "
"reveling instead in the glory of senseless bloodshed and destruction. But "
"there are those amongst their ranks willing to pay heed to the sermons of "
"the Chaos Magi and place their trust in fallen gods from a long forgotten "
"era."
msgstr ""
"Ces soldats noirs se battent pour une cause qu'ils ignorent, la plupart "
"d'entre eux rêvant à la place de bains de sangs et de destruction. Mais il y "
"en a parmi eux qui prêtent une plus grande attention aux sermons des mages "
"du Chaos et qui placent leur foi en des dieux d'une ère depuis longtemps "
"oubliée."

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Invoker, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Invoker.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Invoker"
msgstr "Invocateur du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Invoker, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Invoker.cfg:24
msgid ""
"There is much speculation as to the origins of the religious groups that "
"eventually joined to form the Chaos Empire. Amongst scholars, the most "
"popular theory postulates the creation of two separate cults by the same "
"prophet approximately four centuries ago: the cult of Yechnagoth, centered "
"around the western seaboard, and the cult of Chaos, which existed primarily "
"throughout the eastern wastes.\n"
"\n"
"As time went on, the more prolific Chaos Magi’s sphere of influence expanded "
"and absorbed Yechnagoth’s worshipers, reshaping their tenets and giving way "
"to a unified religion worshiping Uria as the goddess who brought the Dark "
"Lady back from the dead.\n"
"\n"
"Low-ranking initiates — colloquially known as “Invokers” by their enemies — "
"lack the sophisticated knowledge that defines their order; they have much "
"yet to learn before they can attain a formal title and be entrusted with the "
"leadership of the demonic hordes. Nonetheless, they are a cornerstone of the "
"Chaos military, always ready to provide their services and proselytize to "
"captives and outsiders with elaborate displays of power."
msgstr ""
"Il y a beaucoup de spéculation concernant les origines des groupes religieux "
"qui devaient finalement s'unir pour former l'Empire du Chaos. D'après les "
"érudits, la théorie la plus populaire propose la création de deux cultes "
"séparés par le même prophète quatre siècles auparavant : le culte de "
"Yechnagoth, centré sur les littoraux occidentaux, et le culte du Chaos, "
"situé dans les terres désolées orientales.\n"
"\n"
"Au fil du temps, la sphère d'influence des mages du Chaos les plus "
"prolifiques s'étendit et absorba les fidèles de Yechnagoth, reformant leurs "
"principes et ouvrant la voie à une religion unifiée vénérant Uria comme la "
"déesse qui ramena la Dame Noire des griffes de la mort.\n"
"\n"
"Les initiés de rang inférieur — désignés 'invocateur du chaos' par leurs "
"ennemis — n'ont pas la connaissance sophistiquée qui définit leur ordre ; "
"ils ont beaucoup à apprendre avant d'obtenir un titre et de se voir confier "
"le commandement des hordes démoniaques. Toutefois, ils restent des pièces "
"essentielles de l'armée du Chaos, toujours prêts à fournir leur service pour "
"convertir prisonniers et étrangers avec des démonstrations élaborées de "
"puissance."

#. [attack]: type=arcane
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Invoker.cfg:49
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Invoker_Lorekeeper.cfg:63
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Invoker_Magus.cfg:46
msgid "ethereal blast"
msgstr "explosion éthérée"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Lorekeeper, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Invoker_Lorekeeper.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Lorekeeper"
msgstr "Gardien du savoir du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Lorekeeper, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Invoker_Lorekeeper.cfg:26
msgid ""
"In a world where savage men fight each other over what little water and food "
"they can find, knowledge remains one of the few tools left to bring a "
"semblance of order to their pathetic lives. But humans can only do so much "
"to change the flawed reality in which they dwell, and their chaotic, vicious "
"nature surfaces at every turn. The cultists of Chaos believe that only Uria, "
"Mother of all demons, Goddess of Life and Mistress of the Void, can reshape "
"and improve this decaying world. They dedicate their very souls to doing her "
"bidding and spreading her message to every corner of Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"The dreaded Chaos Lorekeepers govern both the military and their subordinate "
"Magi. They are indisputably regarded as sacred figures akin to demigods by "
"Uria’s and Yechnagoth’s worshippers alike. Their dedication to their craft "
"borders on irrational, and the wars they wage often serve much darker "
"purposes. Those unlucky enough to survive are taken captive, fated to "
"undergo unfathomable horrors in the name of the Lorekeepers’ unending search "
"for knowledge. It is this, more than anything else, that keeps their "
"subjects in line; they are well aware of the consequences should they "
"disobey an order even slightly.\n"
"\n"
"But as unlikely as it might sound, the Lorekeepers are not alone in ruling "
"over the wicked legions of Uria..."
msgstr ""
"Dans un monde où des hommes sauvages se battent pour le peu d'eau et de "
"nourriture qu'ils peuvent trouver, le savoir reste l'un des quelques moyens "
"restants pour apporter un semblant d'ordre dans leur vies pathétiques. Mais "
"les humains ne peuvent faire mieux que tenter de changer leur réalité "
"quotidienne, et leur nature chaotique et vicieuse refait surface chaque "
"fois. Les cultistes du Chaos croient que seule Uria, Mère de tous les "
"démons, Déesse de la Vie et Maîtresse du Vide, peut remodeler et améliorer "
"ce monde en déclin. Ils dédient leurs âmes entières à son service et à "
"répandre son message dans tous les recoins d'Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Les redoutés gardiens du savoir du chaos gouvernent aussi bien les "
"militaires que leurs mages subordonnés. Ils sont indiscutablement vus comme "
"des figures sacrées à l'égal de demi-dieux, aussi bien par les fidèles "
"d'Uria que ceux de Yechnagoth. Leur dévotion à leur devoir va jusqu'à "
"l'irrationnel, et les guerres qu'ils mènent servent de bien plus noirs "
"desseins. Les infortunés qui survivent sont capturés et soumis à des "
"horreurs sans nom au nom de la soif de connaissances des gardiens du savoir. "
"C'est cela, plus qu'autre chose, qui maintient leurs sujets dans le rang; "
"ils sont trop bien conscients des conséquences de la moindre désobéissance.\n"
"\n"
"Mais aussi terrifiants qu'ils puissent être, les gardiens du savoir du chaos "
"ne sont pas les seuls à diriger les légions maudites d'Uria..."

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Magus, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Invoker_Magus.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Magus"
msgstr "Démoniste du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Magus, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Invoker_Magus.cfg:25
msgid ""
"When not busy sermonising their devout followers, the Chaos Magi put their "
"craft to use supporting the Empire’s troops with fearsome infernal magic. "
"The power they wield comes at a cost, however, as their bodies gradually "
"succumb to a force not meant for humans to control, rendering them more "
"vulnerable to certain forms of magic. Thus, researching new methods to elude "
"death becomes paramount if they are to achieve — or surpass — the greatness "
"of their elders."
msgstr ""
"Quand ils ne sont pas occupés à sermonner leurs fervents adeptes, les "
"démonistes du Chaos mettent leur talent à profit des troupes de l'Empire "
"avec leur terrifiante magie infernale. Le pouvoir qu'ils manient a toutefois "
"un prix, au fur et à mesure que leurs corps succombent à une force que les "
"hommes n'étaient pas destinés à contrôler, les rendant plus vulnérables à "
"certaines formes de magie. Ainsi, rechercher de nouvelles méthodes pour "
"échapper à la mort devient primordial pour atteindre — ou surpasser — la "
"grandeur de leurs aînés."

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Longbowman, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Longbowman.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Longbowman"
msgstr "Grand archer du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Longbowman, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Longbowman.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Even though the Chaos Empire’s soldiers are more adept at fighting hand-to-"
"hand, they also understand the importance of being able to keep their "
"adversaries at bay and take them down before they can retaliate. Chaos "
"Longbowmen carry more powerful weapons than the average archer; the subtle "
"improvements made to their bows and arrowheads enable their projectiles to "
"fly farther and penetrate even thick armor. Making matters worse are the "
"lethal fluids of dubious origin into which the arrows are dipped prior to "
"shooting."
msgstr ""
"Même si les soldats de l'Empire du Chaos sont plus doués pour le combat au "
"corps-à-corps, ils comprennent également l'importance de la capacité à tenir "
"l'adversaire à distance et de l'achever avant qu'il ne récupère. Les grands "
"archers du Chaos ont des armes plus puissantes que l'archer moyen ; les "
"subtiles améliorations de leurs arcs et flèches permettent à leurs "
"projectiles d'aller plus loin et de percer la plus épaisse des armures. Ce "
"qui les rend encore plus dangereuses sont les fluides mortels d'origine "
"douteuse dans lesquels ils trempent leurs flèches avant de tirer."

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Heavy Longbowman, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Longbowman_Heavy.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Heavy Longbowman"
msgstr "Maître archer du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Heavy Longbowman, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Longbowman_Heavy.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Reloading and aiming is a time-consuming process and a window of opportunity "
"for assailants to strike down the defenseless archer. The most valued bowmen "
"in the Chaos Empire’s service earn their prestige by attaining an elf-like "
"proficiency with the longbow, shooting more than a dozen arrows a minute "
"without tiring or missing their mark — or so the rumors go, anyway."
msgstr ""
"Recharger et viser est un processus long ainsi qu'une fenêtre d'opportunité "
"pour les assaillants d'abattre ces archers sans défense. Les plus valeureux "
"archers de l'Empire du Chaos acquièrent leur prestige en atteignant la "
"vitesse d'exécution d'un elfe avec l'arc long, tirant plus d'une douzaine de "
"flèche à la minute sans se fatiguer ou manquer leur cible — c'est ce que "
"disent les rumeurs en tout cas."

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Marauder, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Marauder.cfg:5
msgid "Marauder"
msgstr "Maraudeur"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Marauder, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Marauder.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Even barbarian brutes can hone their skills given enough time. Those in the "
"Chaos Empire’s service who manage to survive long enough to do so are given "
"plenty of opportunities to broaden their horizons and brandish better arms "
"against their adversaries."
msgstr ""
"Même les brutes les plus barbares peuvent perfectionner leur maîtrise du "
"combat avec suffisamment de temps. Ceux au service de l'Empire du Chaos qui "
"survivent assez longtemps obtiennent nombre d'opportunités pour élargir leur "
"horizons et brandir de meilleures armes contre leurs adversaires."

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Raider, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Raider.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Raider"
msgstr "Pillard du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Raider, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Raider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"For most desert dwellers, horses and other equines have become an "
"increasingly scarce commodity, to the point that they are used in battle "
"only as a last resort in the direst of situations. This is not the case for "
"the Chaos Empire, however, which somehow maintains a steady supply of horses "
"for their numerous raiding parties. Those unaccustomed to the animals "
"usually flee before them, their impressions not improved by the creatures’ "
"fierce disposition and tendency to trample anything underfoot."
msgstr ""
"Pour la plupart des nomades du désert, chevaux et autres équidés sont des "
"commodités en raréfaction, au point de ne s'en servir au combat qu'en "
"dernier recours dans la pire des situations. Toutefois, ce n'est pas le cas "
"de l'Empire du Chaos, puisqu'ils maintiennent une forte réserve de chevaux "
"pour leurs raids. Ceux qui ne sont pas habitués aux animaux fuient devant "
"eux, leur permettant d'éviter la disposition violente de ces créatures et "
"leur tendance à tout piétiner avec leurs sabots."

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Razerman, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Razerman.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Razerman"
msgstr "Razzieur du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Razerman, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Razerman.cfg:29
msgid ""
"To become legion commanders in the Chaos army, soldiers must shed what "
"little remains of their humanity and thoroughly embrace the bloodshed, "
"becoming relentless killing machines. But these demon-like creatures rarely "
"content themselves with simply murdering every living thing in their way. "
"Instead, they take great delight in inflicting as much pain as possible on "
"their hapless victims, with methods such as flaying and mutilation "
"comprising only a small part of their repertoire. Their sadism is rivaled "
"only by that of the Chaos Lorekeepers, and the Mother of Inferno herself."
msgstr ""
"Pour devenir commandants d'une légion dans l'armée du Chaos, les soldats "
"doivent abandonner le peu d'humanité qu'il leur reste pour devenir de "
"véritables machines à tuer. Mais ces êtres se contentent rarement de tuer. "
"Ils se délectent même d'infliger autant de souffrance que possible à leurs "
"victimes impuissantes, l'écorchement et les mutilations n'étant qu'une "
"fraction de leur répertoire. Leur sadisme n'est égalé que par celui des "
"gardiens du savoir du Chaos et par la Mère d'Inferno en personne."

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Soulhunter, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Soulhunter.cfg:5
msgid "Soulhunter"
msgstr "Chasseur d'âmes"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Soulhunter, race=human
#: Naia/units/humans/Chaos_Soulhunter.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Most human civilizations throughout history have held the dead in great "
"respect regardless of their origin and allegiance. Once society crumbled "
"after the Fall, however, it became relatively increasingly common for humans "
"to desecrate the bodies of their deceased for purposes ranging from the "
"practical to the obscene.\n"
"\n"
"Higher-ranking Chaos brutes flaunt their strength and experience by daubing "
"the blood of their fallen enemies on their visages and torsos, and wearing "
"their bones as necklaces, face masks, and other ornamental gear. Dubbed "
"“Soulhunters” by their equally amoral peers, they relish the thrill of "
"battle and are more than willing to put their lives on the line in the hope "
"that, some day, Uria will reward them with unending life and godlike "
"strength to rule over all on Irdya."
msgstr ""
"La plupart des civilisations humaines d'Irdya respectaient les morts quel "
"que soit leurs origines ou leurs allégeances. Une fois la société effondrée "
"après la Chute, toutefois, il devint de plus en plus commun chez les humains "
"de profaner les cadavres pour des raisons pratiques ou simplement obscènes.\n"
"\n"
"Les brutes du Chaos de haut rang marquent leur force et leur expérience en "
"se peignant le visage et le torse avec le sang de leurs ennemis, et en "
"portant leurs os comme colliers, masques faciaux et autres ornements. "
"Qualifiés de \"chasseurs d'âmes” par leurs pairs tout aussi amoraux, ils se "
"délectent du frisson de la bataille et sont plus que ravis de mettre leur "
"vie en jeu dans l'espoir, qu'un jour, Uria les récompense avec une vie "
"éternelle et une force divine pour régner sur tout Irdya."

#. [race]: id=imps
#: Naia/units/imps.cfg:5
msgid "race^Imp"
msgstr "Diablotin"

#. [race]: id=imps
#: Naia/units/imps.cfg:6
msgid "race+female^Imp"
msgstr "Diablotine"

#. [race]: id=imps
#: Naia/units/imps.cfg:7
msgid "race^Imps"
msgstr "Diablotins"

#. [race]: id=imps
#: Naia/units/imps.cfg:8
msgid ""
"Lesser demons are frequently and incorrectly classified in a separate group "
"of their own. Although they generally lack the magic abilities and "
"intellectual power of their better known relatives, their numbers and raw "
"strength usually suffice to compensate."
msgstr ""
"Les démons inférieurs sont fréquemment et incorrectement classifiés dans un "
"groupe à part. Bien qu'il leur manque les capacités magiques et "
"l'intelligence de leurs confrères mieux connus, leur nombre et leur force "
"brute suffisent habituellement à compenser."

#. [unit_type]: id=Armageddon Imp, race=imps
#: Naia/units/imps/Armageddon.cfg:5
msgid "Armageddon Imp"
msgstr "Diablotin d'Armageddon"

#. [unit_type]: id=Armageddon Imp, race=imps
#: Naia/units/imps/Armageddon.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Although most would find the notion preposterous, the truth is that imps "
"larger than the biggest of trolls do exist. These behemoths rarely make an "
"appearance on the battle field, but when they do, they announce themselves "
"with roars able to shake mountains, and stomps that fracture and sink down "
"the ground beneath. One has to wonder exactly how the Chaos Overlords — "
"comically puny by comparison — manage to rein in these titans and have them "
"do their bidding without using any kind of mind-control magic."
msgstr ""
"Bien que le terme puisse sembler prétentieux, la vérité est que ces "
"diablotins sont plus massifs que le plus grand troll qui puisse exister. Ils "
"apparaissent rarement sur le champ de bataille mais quand ça arrive, ces "
"béhémoths s'annoncent en poussant des rugissements capables de fracturer "
"jusqu'aux montagnes mêmes et de s'enfoncer dans la faille ainsi formée "
"jusqu'aux profondeurs du monde. On est en droit de se demander comment les "
"haut seigneurs du Chaos, ridiculement petits face à eux, parviennent à "
"diriger ces titans sans aucune sorte de contrôle magique de l'esprit."

#. [attack]: type=blade
#: Naia/units/imps/Armageddon.cfg:28
msgid "blade of doom"
msgstr "lame de désolation"

#. [attack]: type=pierce
#: Naia/units/imps/Armageddon.cfg:40 Naia/units/imps/Gutwrencher.cfg:40
msgid "slime spit"
msgstr "crachat"

#. [unit_type]: id=Blood Imp, race=imps
#: Naia/units/imps/Blood.cfg:5
msgid "Blood Imp"
msgstr "Diablotin sanguinaire"

#. [unit_type]: id=Blood Imp, race=imps
#: Naia/units/imps/Blood.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Most imps do not enjoy a particularly long lifespan, in no small part due to "
"their demon overlords being all too prone to regarding them as disposable "
"canon fodder. It is no small feat for an imp to survive past childhood, and "
"those who do become a much more credible threat to Irdyan creatures."
msgstr ""
"La plupart des diablotins ne profitent pas d'une longue vie, en grande "
"partie à cause de leurs seigneurs démons trop prompts à les voir comme de la "
"chair à canon. Ce n'est pas rien pour un diablotin de survivre à l'enfance, "
"et ceux qui y parviennent deviennent des ennemis bien plus crédibles pour "
"les créatures Irdyennes."

#. [unit_type]: id=Gutwrencher Imp, race=imps
#: Naia/units/imps/Gutwrencher.cfg:5
msgid "Gutwrencher Imp"
msgstr "Diablotin étripeur"

#. [unit_type]: id=Gutwrencher Imp, race=imps
#: Naia/units/imps/Gutwrencher.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Adult imps come in many forms and sizes, betraying the fact that they are "
"neither related to the better-known demon warriors, nor belonging to a "
"single species of their own. They are much stronger and sharper of mind than "
"it is generally expected of their kind, to the point that it is not unheard "
"of for them to lead some of their demon cousins in battle.\n"
"\n"
"‘Gutwrenchers’ are renowned for their great appetite, and their razor-sharp "
"claws which allow them to swiftly tear their prey to bits. For any hapless "
"creature targeted by one of these monsters there is little hope — even if "
"they somehow manage to extricate themselves from the imp’s crushing grip, "
"odds are their flesh is already melting away thanks to the imp’s corrosive "
"saliva."
msgstr ""
"Les diablotins adultes possèdent plusieurs formes et tailles, trahissant le "
"fait qu'ils ne sont pas liés aux guerriers démons bien mieux connus, ni "
"qu'ils constituent une seule espèce à part. Ils sont plus forts et ont "
"l'esprit bien plus aiguisé que l'on ne s'y attend de la part de leur race, "
"au point qu'il n'est pas rare d'entendre parler d'eux menant certains de "
"leur cousins démons à la bataille.\n"
"\n"
"Les ‘étripeurs’ sont renommés pour leur grand appétit, et leurs griffes "
"acérées comme des lames de rasoir leur permettent de réduire leur proie en "
"charpie. Pour toute créature traquée par ces monstres, il y a peu d'espoir, "
"même si certaines parviennent à se dégager de leurs griffes, leurs chairs "
"étant probablement déjà rongées par leur salive corrosive."

#. [unit_type]: id=Imp, race=imps
#: Naia/units/imps/Imp.cfg:5
msgid "Imp"
msgstr "Diablotin"

#. [unit_type]: id=Imp, race=imps
#: Naia/units/imps/Imp.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Frequently — and incorrectly — considered a lesser class of creatures "
"separate from the fearsome demons, Imps are often underestimated due to "
"their smaller builds and evident lack of of mental prowess. Furthering this "
"misconception, Demon leaders often dispatch them in large numbers as cheap "
"cannon-fodder."
msgstr ""
"Fréquemment — et incorrectement — considérés comme une classe à part et "
"inférieure aux démons, les diablotins sont souvent sous-estimés à cause de "
"leur plus faible constitution et de leur manque évident d'intelligence. Les "
"meneurs démons renforcent cette interprétation en les envoyant souvent en "
"grand nombre servir de chair à canon."

#. [unit_type]: id=Minor Imp, race=imps
#: Naia/units/imps/Minor.cfg:5
msgid "Minor Imp"
msgstr "Diablotin mineur"

#. [unit_type]: id=Minor Imp, race=imps
#: Naia/units/imps/Minor.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Imp whelps are extremely small and frail, and pose no threat whatsoever to "
"any properly-trained soldier. However, coming across a swarm of these "
"creatures spells trouble regardless, as they almost never stray too far away "
"from their progenitors."
msgstr ""
"Les jeunes diablotins sont extrêmement petits et faibles, et ne posent aucun "
"problème à un soldat bien entraîné. Toutefois, approcher une bande de ces "
"créatures attire les ennuis étant donné qu'ils ne sont jamais très loin de "
"leurs parents."

#. [unit_type]: id=Automaton, race=mechanical
#: Naia/units/mechanical/Automaton.cfg:5
msgid "Automaton"
msgstr "Automate"

#. [unit_type]: id=Automaton, race=mechanical
#: Naia/units/mechanical/Automaton.cfg:32
msgid ""
"These small metallic beings seem not to require food or water to fight, very "
"much like the undead. Heavily armored and wielding a steel mace and "
"rectangular shield, these ‘automatons’ are said to have been originally "
"created by the dwarves before a clan was captured by the forces of Chaos. "
"Their primary drawback is their apparent unease when navigating rough "
"terrains such as hills and mountains."
msgstr ""
"Ces petites bêtes métalliques ne semblent pas avoir besoin de nourriture ou "
"d'équivalent pour vivre, comme les morts-vivants. Lourdement blindés, armés "
"d'une dangereuse massue d'acier et d'un bouclier rectangulaire, ces "
"« automates » auraient à l'origine été créés par les nains avant qu'un de "
"leurs clans ne soit capturé par les forces du Chaos. Ils se déplacent assez "
"rapidement malgré leur poids, un mystère que personne n'a encore réussi à "
"élucider. Leur seul inconvénient est leur manque manifeste d'agilité pour se "
"déplacer en terrains accidentés comme les collines et les montagnes."

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: Naia/units/mechanical/Automaton.cfg:49
msgid "rectangular shield"
msgstr "Bouclier rectangulaire"

#. [unit_type]: id=Door, race=mechanical
#: Naia/units/mechanical/Door.cfg:5
msgid "Door"
msgstr "Porte"

#. [unit_type]: id=Door, race=mechanical
#: Naia/units/mechanical/Door.cfg:22
msgid ""
"The door will open only to those who are allied with its owners, unless "
"struck down by their enemies first."
msgstr ""
"La porte ne s'ouvrira qu'aux alliés, sauf si des ennemis la défoncent "
"d'abord."

#. [unit_type]: id=Goliath, race=mechanical
#: Naia/units/mechanical/Goliath.cfg:5
msgid "Mechanical Goliath"
msgstr "Goliath mécanique"

#. [unit_type]: id=Goliath, race=mechanical
#: Naia/units/mechanical/Goliath.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Giant metallic beasts under the command of the forces of Chaos, the "
"Mechanical Goliaths can crush in a matter of seconds any man, skeleton, or "
"even troll. They seem immune to poison, drain, and other hazards that would "
"normally pose a great danger for a living being. Because of this, it’s been "
"suggested that they are magically animated constructions of rock and steel.\n"
"\n"
"To make things even worse, it is said that they can destroy entire armies "
"from a distance with a sudden flash of red light, in an attack that is both "
"powerful and accurate."
msgstr ""
"Ces bêtes métalliques géantes au service de l'Empire du Chaos peuvent "
"écraser n'importe quel humain, squelette ou troll en quelques secondes. "
"Elles se révèlent insensibles au poison, au drain ou autre menace qui "
"affecterait les êtres vivants. À cause de ça, on suggère que ce seraient en "
"réalité des statues de fer et d'acier animées par magie.\n"
"\n"
"De plus, il est dit qu'elles pourraient détruire une armée entière à "
"distance avec une sorte d'éclair rouge, une attaque à la fois puissante et "
"précise."

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: Naia/units/mechanical/Goliath.cfg:52 Naia/units/mechanical/Iron_Golem.cfg:51
msgid "flash cannon"
msgstr "canon laser"

#. [unit_type]: id=Iron Golem, race=mechanical
#: Naia/units/mechanical/Iron_Golem.cfg:5
msgid "Iron Golem"
msgstr "Golem de fer"

#. [unit_type]: id=Iron Golem, race=mechanical
#: Naia/units/mechanical/Iron_Golem.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Some automatons mysteriously grow in size overnight, gaining greater "
"strength and taller bodies in a process that is unknown to anyone but the "
"less commonly seen Lorekeepers of Chaos. They drop their shield and mace in "
"favor of harder and stronger armor, and fists that can crush the rock with "
"minimal effort — compensating for the lack of close range weapons.\n"
"\n"
"Less commonly, they may fire a powerful weapon that is said to resemble the "
"great firesticks of the dwarven lords in both shape and destructive effect. "
msgstr ""
"Certains automates grandissent de façon mystérieuse pendant la nuit, gagnant "
"en force et en stature suite à un processus connu seulement des élusifs "
"gardiens du savoir du Chaos. Leur peau s'épaississant, devenant plus "
"résistante, et leur poing — capable d'écraser un rocher grand comme un homme "
"— devenant une arme à part entière, ils abandonnent leur bouclier "
"rectangulaire et leur masse.\n"
"\n"
" Ils arborent parfois également une étrange arme tubulaire ressemblant aux "
"bâtons de feu des seigneurs nains à la fois dans leurs formes et leurs "
"effets destructeurs. "

#. [unit_type]: id=Worker Droid, race=mechanical
#: Naia/units/mechanical/Worker_Droid.cfg:5
msgid "Worker Droid"
msgstr "Droïde travailleur"

#. [unit_type]: id=Worker Droid, race=mechanical
#: Naia/units/mechanical/Worker_Droid.cfg:33
msgid ""
"These tiny metal gnomes are known as the ‘worker droids’ by the Chaos "
"overlords. It is not known what nature drives their acts; in fact, nobody "
"knows, aside from their creators, if they are living beings, undead, or "
"animated rocks."
msgstr ""
"Les dirigeants du Chaos connaissent ces minuscules gnomes métalliques sous "
"le nom de « travailleurs droïdes ». On ne sait pas quelle nature inspire "
"leurs actes. Excepté leurs créateurs, en réalité personne ne sait s'ils sont "
"vivants, morts-vivants, ou simplement des rochers animés."

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: Naia/units/mechanical/Worker_Droid.cfg:41
msgid "oil"
msgstr "huile"

#. [unit_type]: id=Abomination, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Abomination.cfg:5
msgid "Abomination"
msgstr "Abomination"

#. [unit_type]: id=Abomination, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Abomination.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The origin of these hideous creatures is uncertain. Some speculate that they "
"might be humans, orcs, dwarves or trolls that were somehow changed into "
"their current aspect. Others claim that they are failed attempts at breeding "
"a new race of demon soldiers by the Chaos forces.\n"
"\n"
"However they came into existence, they appear to be highly sensitive to "
"light and avoid leaving the safety of their dark caverns."
msgstr ""
"L'origine de ces créatures hideuses est incertaine. Certains spéculent que "
"ce seraient des humains, orcs, nains ou trolls dont l'aspect a été "
"transformé. D'autres soutiennent que ce sont de vaines tentatives des forces "
"du Chaos de créer une nouvelle race de démons soldats.\n"
"\n"
"Qu'importe la façon dont ils sont apparus, ils semblent hautement sensibles "
"à la lumière et évitent de quitter la sécurité de leurs sombres cavernes."

#. [unit_type]: id=Fire Wisp, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Fire_Wisp.cfg:5
msgid "Fire Wisp"
msgstr "Feu follet"

#. [unit_type]: id=Fire Wisp, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Fire_Wisp.cfg:25
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Fire Wisps are spirits of smoke and flame. When not being ordered around "
"they like to frolic in pools of lava and take great delight in burning "
"anything they can reach."
msgstr ""
"Les feux follets sont des esprits mineurs faits de flammes. Ils aiment "
"batifoler dans des lacs de lave, et prennent beaucoup de plaisir à brûler "
"tout ce qu'ils peuvent toucher. Ils ne devraient pas représenter un gros "
"défi pour des combattants inexpérimentés, à moins qu'ils ne viennent en "
"foule."

#. [attack]: type=fire
#: Naia/units/monsters/Fire_Wisp.cfg:50
msgid "fire bash"
msgstr "frappe de feu"

#. [unit_type]: id=Fungoid, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Fungoid.cfg:5
msgid "Fungoid"
msgstr "Fongueux"

#. [unit_type]: id=Fungoid, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Fungoid.cfg:30
msgid ""
"Fungoids are mushroom-like creatures that can multiply very quickly. Their "
"soft bodies and delicious taste once seasoned make them a prime target for "
"inexperienced adventurers."
msgstr ""
"Les fongueux sont des créatures à l'aspect de champignon se multipliant très "
"rapidement. Leur corps doux et leur goût en font des proies de choix pour "
"des aventuriers inexpérimentés."

#. [unit_type]: id=Lesser Giant Spider, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Giant_Spider_Lesser.cfg:5
msgid "Lesser Giant Spider"
msgstr "Araignée presque géante"

#. [unit_type]: id=Lesser Giant Spider, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Giant_Spider_Lesser.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Smaller and weaker Giant Spiders are very common underground. They usually "
"prey on single insects roaming around, but sometimes it is possible to find "
"dwarven or human corpses trapped in their webs, which suggests they have "
"little problem in eating big individuals fool enough to fall in their traps."
msgstr ""
"Des araignées plus petites et plus faibles que les araignées géantes sont "
"courantes dans les sous-sols. Leurs proies sont généralement des insectes "
"rôdant dans les environs, mais il arrive parfois que des corps d'humains ou "
"de nains soient retrouvés piégés dans leurs toiles, ce qui prouve que manger "
"des êtres plus grands qui se seraient laissés prendre à leur piège ne leur "
"cause que peu de problèmes."

#. [unit_type]: id=Leech, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Leech.cfg:5
msgid "Leech"
msgstr "Sangsue"

#. [unit_type]: id=Leech, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Leech.cfg:45
msgid ""
"Leeches are universally known for their common diet, the warm blood of "
"various bigger creatures. However, this is exactly why they are often used "
"for medicinal purposes.\n"
"\n"
"Although not directly related, the same name is applied to groups of strange "
"worms attached to the ground, found under caves, who are not a great danger "
"as they cannot move around to search for prey. Instead, they await unwary "
"victims who get close enough for them to be able to trap them in their "
"deadly tentacles and then swallow their blood, which increases their "
"strength and heals their wounds.\n"
"\n"
"It is fortunate that they have not developed legs; otherwise, they would be "
"an almost unstoppable menace to explorers and dwellers of the caves they "
"inhabit."
msgstr ""
"Les sangsues sont universellement connues pour leur régime : le sang encore "
"chaud de diverses créatures. C'est d'ailleurs pourquoi elles sont souvent "
"utilisées en médecine.\n"
"\n"
"Bien qu'ils n'aient aucun lien de parenté direct, un groupe d'étranges vers "
"fixé sur le sol des cavernes porte le même nom. Ne pouvant pas se déplacer "
"pour chercher leurs proies, ils ne représentent pas un grand danger. Au lieu "
"de ça, ils attendent une victime inattentive qui serait assez proche pour "
"qu'ils puissent l'attraper de leurs tentacules et sucer son sang, ce qui "
"augmente leurs forces et soigne leurs blessures.\n"
"\n"
"Il est heureux qu'ils n'aient pas développé de jambes, sans quoi ils "
"seraient une menace implacable pour les explorateurs et les habitants des "
"profondeurs."

#. [attack]: type=pierce
#: Naia/units/monsters/Leech.cfg:59
msgid "drainer"
msgstr "suceur"

#. [unit_type]: id=Animated Rock, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Rock_Animated.cfg:5
msgid "Animated Rock"
msgstr "Rocher animé"

#. [unit_type]: id=Animated Rock, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Rock_Animated.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Animated Rocks are rather slow creatures made out of solid, living rock. "
"They have a weak attack, but are incredibly hard to destroy. It is rumored "
"that these magical constructs can only be summoned by powerful magi."
msgstr ""
"Les rochers animés sont des créatures plutôt lentes, faites de pierre. Ils "
"ne sont pas dangereux outre mesure, mais sont extrêmement difficiles à "
"détruire. Il paraît que ces golems ne peuvent être invoqués que par une "
"puissante magie."

#. [unit_type]: id=Rock Golem, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Rock_Golem.cfg:5
msgid "Rock Golem"
msgstr "Golem de pierre"

#. [unit_type]: id=Rock Golem, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Rock_Golem.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Rock Golems are giant, slow, and heavy creatures made out of solid, living "
"rock. Their fists can crush any skeleton in matter of seconds."
msgstr ""
"Les golems de pierres sont de très grandes, lentes et lourdes créatures "
"constituées de roche solide. Leur poing peut écraser n'importe quel "
"squelette en quelques secondes."

#. [unit_type]: id=Water Spirit, gender=female, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Water_Spirit.cfg:5
msgid "female^Water Spirit"
msgstr "Esprit des eaux"

#. [unit_type]: id=Water Spirit, gender=female, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Water_Spirit.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Tidal waves of water have been known to acquire their own consciousness and "
"mind and break free of their summoners’ influence. The result is a more "
"corporeal water being, embodying the might and whim of the water and its "
"denizens."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: Naia/units/monsters/Water_Spirit.cfg:25
#: Naia/units/monsters/Water_Tidal.cfg:24
msgid "water punch"
msgstr "torrent"

#. [unit_type]: id=Water Tidal, gender=female, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Water_Tidal.cfg:5
msgid "female^Water Tidal"
msgstr "Onde des eaux"

#. [unit_type]: id=Water Tidal, gender=female, race=monster
#: Naia/units/monsters/Water_Tidal.cfg:20
msgid ""
"It is said that the world is mostly composed of water. It would be natural, "
"then, to conjecture that water may have its own will and that its power can "
"be summoned by expert magi for nefarious purposes."
msgstr ""

#: Naia/units/shaxthal.cfg:4
msgid ""
"Of the many monstrosities comprising the Chaos legions, the most fearsome of "
"them easily are these alien war-beasts known as the ‘Shaxthals’, always "
"present among the front lines when the Overlords choose not to take any "
"prisoners. Their unnatural strength and durable exoskeletons are completely "
"unrivaled by any living creature native to Irdya, and their ability to "
"decimate enemy armies and topple constructions with relative ease makes them "
"an ideal companion for the demon hordes. Those few fools who attempt to "
"fight them head-on almost never survive to tell the tale, as they either get "
"their skulls shattered by a red energy blast originating from the creatures’ "
"maws, or are ripped to shreds in an instant by their teeth and claws."
msgstr ""
"De toutes les monstruosités constituant les légions du Chaos, les plus "
"redoutables sont sans aucun doute ces bêtes de guerre alien connues sous le "
"nom de 'Shaxthals', toujours présentes sur les lignes de front quand les "
"hauts seigneurs décident de ne pas faire de prisonniers. Leur force "
"surnaturelle et leurs exosquelettes durables sont sans égal chez les "
"créatures vivantes natives d'Irdya, et leur capacité à décimer les armées "
"ennemies et détruire les constructions avec une facilité déconcertante en "
"font des alliés idéaux pour les hordes démoniaques. Les rares téméraires qui "
"ont essayé de les affronter n'en ont pratiquement jamais réchappé pour "
"raconter l'histoire, finissant tous pulvérisés par un rayon d'énergie "
"rougeâtre émanant de la gueule des créatures, ou réduits en pièces par leurs "
"griffes et leurs mâchoires."

#. [race]: id=shaxthal, description={SHAXTHAL_RACE_DESCRIPTION}
#: Naia/units/shaxthal.cfg:9
msgid "race^Shaxthal"
msgstr "Shaxthal"

#. [race]: id=shaxthal, description={SHAXTHAL_RACE_DESCRIPTION}
#: Naia/units/shaxthal.cfg:10
msgid "race+female^Shaxthal"
msgstr "Shaxthale"

#. [race]: id=shaxthal, description={SHAXTHAL_RACE_DESCRIPTION}
#: Naia/units/shaxthal.cfg:11
msgid "race^Shaxthals"
msgstr "Shaxthals"

#. [race]: id=shaxthal, description={SHAXTHAL_RACE_DESCRIPTION}
#: Naia/units/shaxthal.cfg:13
msgid ""
"Long before the arrival of humans, an advanced people called the Argazar "
"created a new lifeform combining characteristics from all other creatures "
"known to them. These creatures known as the ‘invincibles’ or ‘Shaxthals’ "
"were originally meant to become the basis for their research into attaining "
"immortality. However, the enemy nation of Rythé forced the Argazar to "
"repurpose their creations for warfare, thus attracting the attention of a "
"mysterious and powerful foe.\n"
"\n"
"Following a devastating strike that poisoned the air and almost completely "
"wiped out their civilization, the remnants of the Argazar found themselves "
"forced to flee to a primitive world “beyond the veil” called Irdya. As life "
"on the surface proved impossible, the Argazar attempted to rebuild their "
"civilization underground. However, the few Shaxthal creatures they brought "
"with them unexpectedly manifested minds of their own and rebelled against "
"their creators. In the process, they began to assimilate the survivors and "
"spawn new generations with new and more sophisticated bodies.\n"
"\n"
"With barely a few dozen Argazars left, they finally found a way to thwart "
"the Shaxthals’ reproductive capabilities, kill the majority of the "
"creatures, and put a few specimens into hibernation for further research. As "
"the last of their people perished, their historians’ hope was that some day "
"a new civilization would emerge and bring the Argazar back to life using the "
"knowledge they recorded into their many crystal glyphs.\n"
"\n"
"Unbeknownst to them, the first race to discover their legacy would have no "
"intention of using any of their findings for good."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Assault Drone, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Assault.cfg:5
msgid "Assault Drone"
msgstr "Drone d'assaut"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Assault Drone, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Assault.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The Shaxthal Assault Drones are among the most effective members of the "
"Chaos Empire’s offensive arsenal. While their more sedentary counterparts — "
"the Sentry Drones — guard the Empire’s strongholds, the Assault Drones’ "
"formidable brute strength and superior mobility make them excellent siege "
"machines. As such, they are found in large numbers amongst the Chaos "
"legions. Many a particularly stubborn foe has succumbed to these creatures’ "
"assault; neither earth nor stone proves an obstacle as they carry out their "
"missions with brutal efficiency."
msgstr ""
"Les drones d'assaut sont parmi les membres les plus efficaces de l'arsenal "
"offensif de l'Empire du Chaos. Alors que leur versions plus sédentaires — "
"les drones sentinelles — protègent les places fortes de l'Empire, les drones "
"d'assaut ont une force brute et une mobilité supérieure faisant d'eux de "
"formidables machines de siège. De fait, ils se trouvent en grand nombre "
"parmi les légions du Chaos. Beaucoup d'ennemis têtus ont succombé aux "
"attaques de ces créatures ; ni la terre ni la roche ne sont des obstacles "
"tandis qu'ils accomplissent leurs missions avec une efficacité brutale."

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Assault.cfg:45
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Crude.cfg:56
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Enforcer.cfg:58
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Protector.cfg:45
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Runner.cfg:43
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Sentry.cfg:54
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fighter_Stormblade.cfg:42
msgid "energy shock"
msgstr "choc d'énergie"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Drone, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Crude.cfg:5
msgid "Drone"
msgstr "Drone"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Drone, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Crude.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Unnatural. Bloodcurdling. Abominations. Of the many words used to describe "
"the mechanical creatures known as the Shaxthals, these are the most often "
"heard. Amongst their many legions, the lowly Drone is by far the most "
"common, yet even it can tear down an enemy in an instant. A menacing hiss "
"echoing through the gloom is enough to herald approaching death, either by "
"the powerful blasts of energy they unleash from their maws or the Chaos "
"legions never far behind.\n"
"\n"
"But among the few accounts that remain of the Shaxthals’ conquests, the most "
"terrifying detail floating creatures of metal, the light glinting off a "
"demonic, unwavering grin as they dispense death from above."
msgstr ""
"Surnaturelles. Assoiffées de sang. Abominations. Des nombreux mots utilisés "
"pour qualifier les créatures mécaniques connues sous le nom de shaxthals, ce "
"sont les plus souvent entendus. Parmi leurs nombreuses légions, les drones "
"inférieurs sont de loin les plus communs, et pourtant ils sont capables de "
"tuer un ennemi en un instant. Un sifflement menaçant est suffisant pour "
"avertir d'une mort imminente, soit par les puissantes explosions "
"énergétiques qu'ils libèrent par leur mâchoire, soit par les légions du "
"Chaos qui ne sont jamais loin derrière.\n"
"\n"
"Mais d'après le peu de survivants des conquêtes shaxthales, le détail le "
"plus terrifiant sur ces créatures de métal flottantes concerne cette lumière "
"démoniaque accompagnant le sourire qu'elles arborent en dispensant la mort."

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Enforcer Drone, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Enforcer.cfg:7
msgid "Enforcer Drone"
msgstr "Drone exécuteur"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Enforcer Drone, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Enforcer.cfg:29
msgid ""
"Bulkier and seemingly smarter versions of the Sentry drones are said to "
"dwell in the deepest reaches of the Shaxthal hives protecting their "
"offspring and territory."
msgstr ""
"Il est dit que des versions plus volumineuses et apparemment plus "
"intelligentes des drones sentinelles rôdent dans les recoins les plus "
"profonds des ruches shaxthales, protégeant leur progéniture et leur "
"territoire."

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Protector Drone, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Protector.cfg:5
msgid "Protector Drone"
msgstr "Drone protecteur"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Protector Drone, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Protector.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Some drones develop their flexibility and deftness more than others. The "
"Protectors have chosen the path of endurance and attack strength, becoming "
"heavier and slower, yet lethal weapons of mass destruction. Their unusual "
"attack accuracy makes them especially dangerous."
msgstr ""
"Certains drones font preuve de plus de flexibilité et d'habileté que les "
"autres. Mais les drones protecteurs ont choisi le chemin de l'endurance et "
"de la puissance d'attaque, devenant certes plus lourds et plus lents, mais "
"également en armes mortelles de destruction massive. Leurs attaques "
"inhabituellement précises les rendent particulièrement dangereux."

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Runner Drone, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Runner.cfg:5
msgid "Runner Drone"
msgstr "Drone coureur"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Runner Drone, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Runner.cfg:17
msgid ""
"These bipedal Shaxthal creatures are better adapted for speed, agility and "
"accuracy at ground level. On their own they don’t pose a great threat, but "
"swarms of these can be highly dangerous."
msgstr ""
"Ces créatures bipèdes shaxthales sont les plus adaptées en vitesse, agilité "
"et précision au sol. Toutes seules, elles ne constituent pas une grande "
"menace, mais en essaims elles peuvent être très dangereuses."

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Sentry Drone, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Sentry.cfg:5
msgid "Sentry Drone"
msgstr "Drone sentinelle"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Sentry Drone, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_Sentry.cfg:25
msgid ""
"From the dark, echoing labyrinths of the Shaxthal hives to the shadowy "
"fortresses of the Chaos Empire await guardians who can neither be swayed by "
"words or gold: the Sentry Drones. Silent and deadly, these sentinels were "
"engineered to quickly and efficiently eliminate any trespassers into the "
"Empire’s domain. Any unlucky enough to attract their attention have but one "
"recourse: flight — that is, if they can outpace them. Should the fleeing "
"intruder fall victim to the drones’ scalding blasts of energy, their vicious "
"teeth and claws will make short work of what remains."
msgstr ""
"Des noirs labyrinthes des ruches shaxthales jusqu'aux tout aussi sombres "
"forteresses de l'Empire du Chaos existent des gardes qui ne peuvent être "
"soudoyés par des paroles ou de l'or : les drones sentinelles. Silencieuses "
"et mortelles, ces sentinelles sont conçues pour éliminer rapidement et "
"efficacement tout intrus dans le domaine impérial. Ceux ayant la malchance "
"d'attirer leur attention n'ont qu'une solution : fuir, s'ils parviennent à "
"les distancer. Si ces intrus sont finissent victimes des attaques "
"énergétiques de ces drones, leurs vicieuses dents et griffes auront vite "
"fait d'en finir avec les restes."

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal War Drone, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_War.cfg:7
msgid "War Drone"
msgstr "Drone de guerre"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal War Drone, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_War.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Recent developments appear to have led to the creation of more advanced "
"types of Shaxthal drones designed for swiftly obliterating front lines and "
"base defenses using aerial strikes. With the frightening accuracy of the "
"Protectors and the formidable strength of Assault drones combined, these "
"notably rare War drones can quickly bring reinforced stone walls down and "
"crush anyone foolish enough to confront them without the use of magic "
"support."
msgstr ""
"Des développements récents semblent avoir permis la création de nouveaux "
"types avancés de drones shaxthals, conçus pour neutraliser rapidement les "
"lignes de front et les bases défensives en utilisant des frappes aériennes. "
"Avec la précision effrayante des protecteurs combinée à la formidable "
"puissance des drones d'assaut, ces drones de guerre particulièrement rares "
"peuvent rapidement abattre un mur de pierre et écraser toute personne assez "
"stupide pour essayer de les arrêter sans recours à la magie."

#. [attack]: type=blade
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_War.cfg:44
msgid "war-blades"
msgstr "lames de guerre"

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Drone_War.cfg:53
msgid "energy burst"
msgstr "éclat d'énergie."

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Razorbird, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fauna_Razorbird.cfg:5
msgid "Razorbird"
msgstr "Rapace de fer"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Razorbird, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fauna_Razorbird.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Since Shaxthal drones began to be regularly spotted in the battle-field, "
"other new biomechanical lifeforms have appeared, seemingly as the result of "
"the Shaxthalkind’s mere presence on Irdya. Amongst those, metallic birds "
"with sharp knives for feathers are frequently seen near the surface "
"entrances of the creatures’ hives. Being clad in metal makes them slower "
"than normal birds, and also more dangerous."
msgstr ""
"Depuis que les drones shaxthals ont commencé à être vus régulièrement sur "
"les champs de bataille, d'autres formes de vie biomécanique ont fait leur "
"apparition, apparemment en raison de la simple présence de la race shaxthale "
"sur Irdya. Parmi celles-ci, des oiseaux métalliques avec des couteaux "
"tranchants en guise de plumes ont pu être observés près de l'entrée en "
"surface des ruches de ces créatures. Couverts de métal, ils sont plus lents "
"que des oiseaux normaux, mais aussi plus dangereux."

#. [attack]: type=pierce
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fauna_Razorbird.cfg:29
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fauna_Thunderbird.cfg:30
msgid "beak"
msgstr "bec"

#. [attack]: type=blade
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fauna_Razorbird.cfg:38
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fauna_Thunderbird.cfg:42
msgid "blade shower"
msgstr "déluge de lames"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Thunderbird, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fauna_Thunderbird.cfg:5
msgid "Thunderbird"
msgstr "Rapace de tonnerre"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Thunderbird, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fauna_Thunderbird.cfg:18
msgid ""
"More advanced bird-like Shaxthal creatures can produce deadly lightning with "
"their sharp feather-blades to attack enemies at a distance, as well as dive "
"and charge into their heads using their powerful metallic beaks."
msgstr ""
"Les créatures shaxthales ailées plus avancées telles que ces oiseaux peuvent "
"produire des éclairs mortels avec leurs lames de plumes acérées pour "
"attaquer leurs ennemis à distance, mais ils peuvent aussi piquer et charger "
"avec leurs têtes en utilisant leurs puissants becs métalliques."

#. [attack]: type=fire
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fauna_Thunderbird.cfg:51
msgid "thunderbolt"
msgstr "éclair"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Worm, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fauna_Worm.cfg:5
msgid "Worm"
msgstr "Ver"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Worm, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fauna_Worm.cfg:54
msgid ""
"Despite being creatures of artificial origins, Shaxthal lifeforms have been "
"reported to vary wildly in shape, size and behavior. Since very little is "
"known about their life cycles, it’s not clear whether certain forms — such "
"as these biomechanical worms — are in reality just different growth stages "
"of the same creature.\n"
"\n"
"The Shaxthal worms dwell inside the great dark hives and they are almost "
"never seen elsewhere. Some evidence gathered and analyzed by scholars would "
"indicate these creatures are extremely vulnerable in the open."
msgstr ""
"En dépit de leur nature d'origine artificielle, les formes de vie shaxthale "
"sont étonnamment variées en forme, en taille et en comportement. A cause du "
"manque cruel de connaissances à propos de leurs cycles de vie, on ne sait "
"pas si certaines formes — telles que ces vers biomécaniques — ne seraient en "
"réalité rien d'autre que des phases de croissance de la même créature.\n"
"\n"
"Les vers shaxthals résident à l'intérieur des grandes ruches sombres et ils "
"ne sont presque jamais signalés ailleurs. Certains éléments recueillis et "
"analysés par des chercheurs semblent indiquer que ces créatures sont "
"extrêmement vulnérables à l'air libre."

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Rayblade, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fighter_Rayblade.cfg:5
msgid "Rayblade"
msgstr "Sabre-laser"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Rayblade, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fighter_Rayblade.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The majority of Shaxthal drones are at best mediocre in close combat, their "
"bodies lacking the precision required for countering blows effectively. As "
"one would expect, the Chaos Lorekeepers realized this and devised a "
"solution: the Shaxthal Rayblades. Not only have they forgone claws and "
"energy blasts in exchange for their namesake arm blades, but they also "
"possess the fearsome ability to spin their torsos rapidly and slice through "
"enemy lines like butter."
msgstr ""
"La majorité des drones shaxthals est au mieux médiocre en combat rapproché, "
"leur corps n'ayant pas la précision requise pour conter les attaques "
"efficacement. Comme on pouvait s'y attendre, les gardiens du savoir du Chaos "
"s'en sont rendu compte et ont créée une solution : Les sabres-laser. Non "
"seulement ils ont délaissé griffes et rayons d'énergie en échange de leurs "
"fameuses lames, mais ils possèdent également la terrifiante capacité de "
"faire tournoyer rapidement leur torse et de trancher à travers les lignes "
"ennemies comme du beurre."

#. [attack]: type=blade
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fighter_Rayblade.cfg:24
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fighter_Stormblade.cfg:31
msgid "weapon^rayblade"
msgstr "sabre-laser"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Stormblade, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fighter_Stormblade.cfg:7
msgid "Stormblade"
msgstr "Sabreur-tempête"

#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Stormblade, race=shaxthal
#: Naia/units/shaxthal/Fighter_Stormblade.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Because of their comparatively expensive design, Stormblade drones are a "
"rarer sight on the battlefield than other Shaxthal creatures. Their deadly "
"long arm-blades combined with the recovered ability to retaliate against "
"ranged attacks makes them extremely dangerous opponents."
msgstr ""
"En raison de leurs armes et armures coûteuses, les sabreurs-tempête sont "
"assez rares sur le champ de bataille comparé aux autres créatures "
"shaxthales. La combinaison de leurs longues lames et de leurs faisceaux de "
"destruction nouvellement réintroduits les rend bien plus dangereux que les "
"autres drones."

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Cardinal, race=undead
#: Naia/units/undead/Chaos_Cardinal.cfg:5
msgid "Chaos Cardinal"
msgstr "Cardinal du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Cardinal, race=undead
#: Naia/units/undead/Chaos_Cardinal.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Two centuries before the birth of the Chaos Empire, its forefathers and "
"their revered Dark Lady found themselves challenged by a barbaric people "
"hailing from the Great Southern Desert: the Quenoth Elves. In spite of the "
"superior weaponry and magic skill at the Iron Council’s disposal, the "
"invaders’ cunning tactics and unrelenting ferocity proved decisive in "
"turning the tide of battle in their favor. And although the Iron Council "
"ultimately repelled their assault, the elves did not abandon the Council’s "
"sanctuary without first taking the life of the most revered priest of "
"Yechnagoth, the de facto leader of the Iron Triad in the absence of their "
"true master.\n"
"\n"
"Over three centuries later, Mal Hekuba continues to roam Irdya carrying out "
"the orders of the living goddess who promises a new era of restoration and "
"unity, in the hope that some day, the Dark Lady will too rise once more and "
"purge all non-believers from this tainted earth."
msgstr ""
"Deux siècles avant l'apparition de l'Empire du Chaos, ses ancêtres et leur "
"vénérée Dame Noire ont été défiés par un peuple barbare provenant du Grand "
"Désert : les Elfes de Quenoth. Malgré les armes et les compétences magiques "
"supérieures du Conseil de Fer, les tactiques ingénieuses et la férocité des "
"envahisseurs leur ont permis de tourner le courant de la bataille en leur "
"faveur. Et bien que le Conseil de Fer ait finalement réussi à repousser leur "
"assaut, les elfes n'ont pas abandonné le sanctuaire du Conseil avant de "
"prendre la vie du prêtre le plus révéré de Yechnagoth, le meneur officieux "
"du Conseil de Fer en l'absence de leur véritable maître.\n"
"\n"
"Trois siècles plus tard, Mal Hekuba continue à arpenter Irdya, accomplissant "
"les ordres de sa déesse bien vivante qui promet une nouvelle ère de "
"restauration et d'unité dans l'espoir qu'un jour, la Dame Noire s'élève elle "
"aussi à nouveau pour purger cette terre maudite de tous les hérétiques."

#. [attack]: type=arcane
#: Naia/units/undead/Chaos_Cardinal.cfg:33
msgid "necrotic shard"
msgstr "éclat nécrotique"

#. [attack]: type=arcane
#: Naia/units/undead/Chaos_Cardinal.cfg:58
msgid "breath of nyx"
msgstr "souffle de nyx"

#. [unit_type]: id=Errant Soul
#: Naia/units/undead/Errant_Soul.cfg:5
msgid "Errant Soul"
msgstr "Âme errante"

#. [unit_type]: id=Errant Soul
#: Naia/units/undead/Errant_Soul.cfg:16
msgid ""
"These lost souls have wandered the barren wastelands of Irdya ever since the "
"Fall, trapped in ethereal bodies that only vaguely resemble their former "
"living appearances."
msgstr ""
"Depuis la Chute, ces âmes perdues errent dans le désert stérile d'Irdya, "
"piégées dans des corps éthérés qui ne ressemblent que vaguement à leur "
"ancienne apparence."

#. [unit_type]: id=Archaic Lich, race=undead
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Archaic_Lich.cfg:5
msgid "Archaic Lich"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Archaic Lich, race=undead
#. [unit_type]: id=Tenebrous Everbane, race=undead
#. [unit_type]: id=Undying Eradicator, race=undead
#. The first two paragraph of this unit type description are shared
#. among three unit types: Archaic Lich, Undying Eradicator, and
#. Tenebrous Everbane.
#. The first two paragraph of this unit type description are shared
#. among three unit types: Archaic Lich, Undying Eradicator, and
#. Tenebrous Everbane.
#. The first two paragraph of this unit type description are shared
#. among three unit types: Archaic Lich, Undying Eradicator, and
#. Tenebrous Everbane.
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Archaic_Lich.cfg:22
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Tenebrous_Everbane.cfg:22
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Undying_Eradicator.cfg:22
msgid ""
"To most denizens of the world of the living, necromancy is synonymous with "
"depravation beyond forgiveness, a violation of the sacred natural order of "
"the cosmos, a practice outlawed by every manner of sapient creature on "
"Irdya. Yet, some purposefully disregard the warnings and dedicate their "
"existence to the pursuit of the forbidden, eager to show the world how "
"breaking free from their shackles of skin and flesh is the path to a greater "
"destiny in a world fraught with decay and ruin.\n"
"\n"
"While many necromancers through the ages have been known to attain lichdom, "
"all of them have ultimately succumbed to the efforts of foolish heroes and "
"their armies seeking to rid Irdya of their blight; all of them, except for "
"one Mal Keshar, who mysteriously resurfaced many times during the Golden Age "
"after—allegedly—having been struck down for good. Some theorize that this "
"necromancer discovered the means to transcend the conventional nature of "
"souls and endure no matter what became of his body — if true, then it is "
"truly for the best that he never passed this knowledge onto others of his "
"ilk."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Archaic Lich, race=undead
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Archaic_Lich.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Following his confrontation with the forest elves under Galas’s command, Mal "
"Keshar’s power is severely limited. While Anlindë has refused to disclose "
"the specifics of the curse she inflicted upon him, she has at least warned "
"the Elven Council of its fragile nature to ensure they are prepared for the "
"very real possibility of him enacting vengeance for such a grave humiliation."
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=arcane
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Archaic_Lich.cfg:37
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Tenebrous_Everbane.cfg:36
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Undying_Eradicator.cfg:37
msgid "touch"
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=cold
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Archaic_Lich.cfg:49
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Undying_Eradicator.cfg:49
msgid "chill tempest"
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=arcane
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Archaic_Lich.cfg:61
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Undying_Eradicator.cfg:61
msgid "shadow wave"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Tenebrous Everbane, race=undead
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Tenebrous_Everbane.cfg:5
msgid "Tenebrous Everbane"
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=cold
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Tenebrous_Everbane.cfg:49
msgid "frostborne erosion"
msgstr ""

#. [attack]: type=arcane
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Tenebrous_Everbane.cfg:62
msgid "calamitous surge"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Undying Eradicator, race=undead
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Undying_Eradicator.cfg:5
msgid "Undying Eradicator"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Undying Eradicator, race=undead
#: Naia/units/undead/Necro_Undying_Eradicator.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Still merely a shadow of his former self, Mal Keshar continues to roam Irdya "
"after the Great Fall seeking to impart curses upon any lesser creatures "
"deserving of his rancor. The elves of the Valley of Elynia are more than "
"aware of his fickle nature, and have devised emergency countermeasures in "
"the event he turns against his temporary allies. Whether Lord Galas’s gamble "
"will pay off in the end is anyone’s guess."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Barrow Wight, race=undead
#: Naia/units/undead/Undead_Horse_Barrow_Wight.cfg:4
msgid "Barrow Wight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Barrow Wight, race=undead
#: Naia/units/undead/Undead_Horse_Barrow_Wight.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Perpetually haunted by the fading memory of its former life, a Barrow Wight "
"wanders aimlessly in a delirium of darkness and despair. Their chill essence "
"is shrouded behind cloak and bone, shielding them from most magic."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Pyre Wight, race=undead
#: Naia/units/undead/Undead_Horse_Pyre_Wight.cfg:4
msgid "Pyre Wight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type]: id=Pyre Wight, race=undead
#: Naia/units/undead/Undead_Horse_Pyre_Wight.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Risen from a funeral’s ashes and newly bathed in fire, a Pyre Wight’s soul "
"burns with a desire for vengeance. They single-mindedly seek out those who "
"wronged them in their past life, but undeath has robbed their memories of "
"friend and foe."
msgstr ""

#. [race]: id=verlissh
#: Naia/units/verlissh.cfg:5
msgid "race^Verlissh"
msgstr "Verlissh"

#. [race]: id=verlissh
#: Naia/units/verlissh.cfg:6
msgid "race+female^Verlissh"
msgstr "Verlissh"

#. [race]: id=verlissh
#: Naia/units/verlissh.cfg:7
msgid "race^Verlisshi"
msgstr "Verlissh"

#. [race]: id=verlissh
#: Naia/units/verlissh.cfg:8
msgid ""
"In order to expand its frontiers and defend its territory more effectively, "
"the Chaos Empire has resorted to summoning all sorts of previously unseen "
"creatures to support its vast military force. Some are said to come from the "
"darkest depths of Irdya; others are rumored to hail from the unknown lands "
"beyond the sky itself. Very little is known for certain about these monsters "
"beyond their evident connection to the Lorekeepers’ arcane arts."
msgstr ""
"Afin d'étendre ses frontières et de défendre ses territoires plus "
"efficacement, l'Empire du Chaos en est venu à invoquer toutes sortes de "
"créatures inconnues jusque là pour renforcer ses armées. Certaines "
"viendraient des profondeurs insondables d'Irdya ; alors que d'autres "
"proviendraient de terres inconnues au-delà du ciel même. On en sait peu sur "
"ces monstres au-delà de leur lien évident avec les arcanes pratiqués par les "
"gardiens du savoir."

#. [unit_type]: id=Verlissh Matrix Core, race=verlissh
#: Naia/units/verlissh/Matrix_Core.cfg:5
msgid "Matrix Core"
msgstr "Cœur matriciel"

#. [unit_type]: id=Verlissh Matrix Core, race=verlissh
#. [unit_type]: id=Verlissh Matrix Flow System, race=verlissh
#: Naia/units/verlissh/Matrix_Core.cfg:27
#: Naia/units/verlissh/Matrix_Flow_System.cfg:28
msgid ""
"These unfathomable, purportedly living constructs are usually found "
"underground near Shaxthal hives. Fully immobile by nature, they have very "
"limited means of self-defense. Given their disproportionate size, they may "
"be a hindrance when found in narrow underground passages."
msgstr ""
"Ces monstrueuses constructions vivantes sont habituellement trouvées sous "
"terre à proximité des ruches shaxthales. Totalement immobiles par nature, "
"elles sont très limitées en autodéfense. À cause de leur taille "
"disproportionnée, elles peuvent être un obstacle à l'entrée des passages "
"souterrains les plus étroits."

#. [attack]: type=cold
#: Naia/units/verlissh/Matrix_Core.cfg:31
#: Naia/units/verlissh/Matrix_Flow_System.cfg:32
#: Naia/units/verlissh/Psy_Crawler.cfg:32
msgid "energy ray"
msgstr "rayon d'énergie"

#. [attack]: type=fire
#: Naia/units/verlissh/Matrix_Core.cfg:40
msgid "hot goo"
msgstr "glue ardente"

#. [unit_type]: id=Verlissh Matrix Flow System, race=verlissh
#: Naia/units/verlissh/Matrix_Flow_System.cfg:5
msgid "Matrix Structural"
msgstr "Matrice structurelle"

#. [attack]: type=pierce
#: Naia/units/verlissh/Matrix_Flow_System.cfg:41
msgid "goo"
msgstr "glue"

#. [unit_type]: id=Psy Crawler, race=verlissh
#: Naia/units/verlissh/Psy_Crawler.cfg:5
msgid "Psy Crawler"
msgstr "Rampeur psy"

#. [unit_type]: id=Psy Crawler, race=verlissh
#: Naia/units/verlissh/Psy_Crawler.cfg:19
msgid ""
"These tentacled creatures are often found underground within Shaxthal hives, "
"wandering aimlessly and preying upon smaller lifeforms when not magically "
"commanded by the dreaded Lorekeepers. Being rather slow and weak, it is very "
"unusual for them to be seen on the surface, and even more unusual for them "
"to be sent away from their habitat."
msgstr ""
"Ces créatures tentaculaires sont souvent trouvées sous terre dans les ruches "
"shaxthales, errant et chassant de petites formes de vie lorsqu'elles ne sont "
"pas contrôlées magiquement par les gardiens du savoir. Étant lents et "
"faibles, il est inhabituel d'en trouver en surface, et encore plus de les "
"envoyer loin de leur habitat."

#. [unit_type]: id=Psy Mindraider, race=verlissh
#: Naia/units/verlissh/Psy_Mindraider.cfg:5
msgid "Psy Mindraider"
msgstr "Razzieur psy"

#. [unit_type]: id=Psy Mindraider, race=verlissh
#: Naia/units/verlissh/Psy_Mindraider.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Assumed to be related to the wandering crawlers at the Lorekeepers’ service, "
"these fearsome creatures are said to have the ability to pierce into the "
"very minds of any living opponents, replenishing their vital energy and "
"accelerating their growth in the process. Needless to say, this makes them "
"especially dangerous to approach."
msgstr ""
"Ces créatures étranges et effrayantes, que l'on suppose invoquées par les "
"gardiens du savoir, ont la capacité de s'attaquer à l'esprit même de leurs "
"opposants pour reconstituer leur propre énergie vitale et croître en force. "
"Inutile de dire que cela les rend particulièrement dangereuses à approcher."

#. [attack]: type=arcane
#: Naia/units/verlissh/Psy_Mindraider.cfg:37
msgid "mind probe"
msgstr "rongement de l'esprit"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Hound, race=wolf
#: Naia/units/wolves/Hound_Chaos.cfg:5
msgid "Hound of Chaos"
msgstr "Chien du Chaos"

#. [unit_type]: id=Chaos Hound, race=wolf
#: Naia/units/wolves/Hound_Chaos.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Exceedingly few communities have continued to breed domesticated dogs after "
"the Fall, not only because of the harsher climate and scarce resources with "
"which to feed captive animals, but also on account of an overabundance of "
"larger and more dangerous predators. The Chaos Empire, on the other hand, "
"not content with using slaves and barbarian mercenaries in warfare, has "
"turned dog breeding into more than a mere pastime. To their quadrupedal "
"companions anything unfamiliar constitutes prey, and these vicious canines "
"never yield in a fight until either their target or themselves has been "
"reduced to bloody bits."
msgstr ""
"Peu de communautés ont continué à élever des chiens domestiques après la "
"Chute, à cause du dur climat et du peu de ressources disponibles pour "
"nourrir des animaux en captivité, mais aussi à cause d'une surabondance de "
"plus grands et plus dangereux prédateurs. L'Empire du Chaos, d'un autre "
"côté, non content d'utiliser des esclaves et des mercenaires barbares pour "
"la guerre, a converti l'élevage de chiens en quelque chose de plus sinistre "
"qu'un simple passe-temps. Pour leurs compagnons quadrupèdes, tout est une "
"proie, et leurs canines vicieuses ne relâchent jamais leur proie durant un "
"combat à moins que leur cible ou elles-mêmes ne soient réduites à une masse "
"sanguinolente."

#. [unit_type]: id=Demonic Hound, race=wolf
#: Naia/units/wolves/Hound_Demonic.cfg:5
msgid "Demonic Hound"
msgstr "Chien démoniaque"

#. [unit_type]: id=Demonic Hound, race=wolf
#: Naia/units/wolves/Hound_Demonic.cfg:25
msgid ""
"It is relatively rare for a Chaos Hound to survive even a year in service on "
"account of their relatively frail build, which makes them prime targets for "
"arrows and sling bullets; and their temperament, which more often than not "
"leads to in-fighting. Those that do, however, quickly earn the Chaos Magi’s "
"attentions — which tend to entail subjecting the beasts to all manner of "
"reprehensible experiments, turning them into sturdier and deadlier killing "
"machines.\n"
"\n"
"It is rumored some Chaos Overlords delight in keeping these hellish hounds "
"as pets. If so, this an even greater deterrent to anyone who would dare "
"enter an Overlord’s stronghold uninvited."
msgstr ""
"Il est relativement rare pour un chien du Chaos de survivre ne serait-ce "
"qu'un an en raison de leur constitution relativement frêle, faisant d'eux "
"des cibles de choix pour les flèches et autres munitions ; sans compter leur "
"tempérament qui les conduit souvent à se quereller mutuellement. Malgré "
"tout, ceux qui survivent attirent rapidement l'attention des mages du chaos "
"— qui ont soumis ces bêtes à toutes sortes d'expériences répréhensibles pour "
"en faire de véritables machines à tuer.\n"
"\n"
"Il existe des rumeurs comme quoi certains hauts seigneurs du chaos adorent "
"garder ces chiens démoniaques comme animaux de compagnie. Si c'est le cas, "
"c'est une dissuasion supplémentaire d'entrer dans une place forte d'un haut "
"seigneur sans y être invité."

#. [unit_type]: id=Hellhound, race=wolf
#: Naia/units/wolves/Hound_Hell.cfg:5
msgid "Hellhound"
msgstr "Chien des enfers"

#. [unit_type]: id=Hellhound, race=wolf
#: Naia/units/wolves/Hound_Hell.cfg:26
msgid ""
"It should come as no surprise to anyone that the followers of Uria have "
"perfected techniques for extracting and transplanting souls. Very little "
"information about it has reached any outsider, but the little extant "
"evidence indicates that it is a common disciplinary action against those who "
"have failed in their missions or otherwise displeased their superiors. They "
"are then given a last chance to clear their names and prove their worth, "
"usually with new bodies seldom fit for the task.\n"
"\n"
"It is suspected that most of the Chaos Hounds who manage to survive their "
"masters’ research have had their souls replaced with those of these fallen "
"demons, either because their original souls break down from the horrors, or "
"simply because it is much easier to strip a tortured soul from its vessel. "
"The denizens of Inferno have found that there could hardly be anything more "
"humiliating than being forced to carry on their lives confined to the bodies "
"of beasts that even their Irdyan allies despise: walking on all fours, "
"sleeping next to their own excrement, and eventually succumbing to their low "
"instincts. Having long since realized that regaining their honor is a lost "
"cause, these miserable creatures determine that there are only two remaining "
"options: either to embrace death at the hands of their enemies, or turn "
"against their masters and pray that they do not decide to prolong the "
"torment."
msgstr ""
"Cela ne devrait surprendre personne que les fidèles d'Uria possèdent des "
"techniques perfectionnées pour extraire et transplanter les âmes. Peu "
"d'informations sont parvenues à l'extérieur de l'Empire, mais les éléments "
"dont on dispose indiquent que c'est une mesure disciplinaire courante envers "
"ceux qui échouent dans leurs missions ou qui ont déplu à leurs supérieurs. "
"On leur laisse alors une dernière chance de laver leur nom et prouver leur "
"valeur, le plus souvent avec un nouveau corps adapté à la tâche.\n"
"\n"
"On suspecte que la plupart des chiens du Chaos qui survivent aux recherches "
"de leurs maîtres ont eu leurs âmes remplacées par celles de ces démons "
"déchus, soit parce que leurs âmes d'origines ont été brisées par ce "
"traitement horrifiant, ou simplement parce qu'il est plus facile d'extraire "
"une âme torturée de son vaisseau. Les citoyens d'Inferno ont découvert qu'il "
"n'y avait rien de plus humiliant qu'être enfermé dans le corps de bêtes que "
"même leurs alliés Irdyens méprisent : marchant à quatre pattes, dormant dans "
"leurs propres excréments, et succombant finalement à leurs plus bas "
"instincts. Ayant compris que retrouver leur honneur est une cause perdue, "
"ces créatures misérables n'ont que deux options : chercher la mort de la "
"main de leurs ennemis, ou se retourner contre leurs maîtres en espérant "
"qu'ils abrègent leurs souffrances."

#~ msgid ""
